Commentary: Sharma starts off with a good length delivery around off, Burns gets his bat down and keeps this one out solidly.
First runs of the morning and England along with Burns open their account now. A good length ball on middle, Burns clips this one to the fine leg region for a single.
Comes 'round the wicket to the right-handed Sibley. Dishes a good length delivery outside the off pole, Sibley just leaves this one alone.
Identical to the last delivery this time and Sibley offers the same shot as he did on the last ball. Which is basically no shot.
Makes Dom play at this one as he bowls it close to the off pole on a good length, Sibley defends this one towards the mid on region.
Good length and on the off pole, Dom plays this one towards mid on again. A tidy start by Ishant. Just the single run off this over.

DROPPED? Looks like it. Pant have to stretch but he does not take this one. Good effort from him. On a length and on sliding down leg, Burns looks to tuck this one but is only able to manage a faint tickle as Pant dives to his right, gets his fingertips to this but is not able to hold on. One run for Rory.
Good length and outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Another length delivery outside off, Sibley, again, offers no shot to this one.
Similar to the last delivery, the ball hits the deck and moves inwards slightly as Dom makes another leave.
On a length and around off, Sibley blocks this one solidly.
Back of a length and around off, Dom pushes this one to the leg side. Bumrah's first over sees him concede just a single run too.
Fuller and outside off, Burns raises his blade and lets this one through to the keeper.
Bowls this one with the angle around the off pole, Burns fends this one out.

Sharma bowls a good length ball on middle, Burns flicks this one through the mid-wicket region and Sundar and Ashwin give it chase. Sundar does well to pull it back before the ropes. Saves one run for his side. Three runs taken.
In that channel outside off, Sibley makes no attempt to play at this. Has not opened his account yet here, has Sibley.
Closer to the off pole on a length, Dom taps this one to point. Says a loud 'no' for the single.
Dom is off the mark now! On a length and around off, Sibley pushes this one to the covers for a quick run.
Quick early call and good running. A length ball on off, Dom dabs this one to the point region and calls Rory for the single. Burns replies and they complete this one nicely.
Just outside the off pole and on a fuller length, Burns has no issues in leaving this one alone.
Two this time. Length and on middle, Burns clips this one to the fine leg region and the openers for the English Lions come back for the second run as well.
Hops and blocks this one towards mid-wicket. 'NO RUNNNNN', says Burns, to Sibley, in regard to the single.
As this one is in the channel outside the off pole, Rory has no problems in letting this one go.
Does what he did on the previous delivery on this one as well. Ends the over with a dot. 3 runs off this over.
Closer to the off stump and around off, Dom offers a solid defense.
On a good length and around the off pole, Sibley works this one towards the mid on region.
On a good length and around that fourth stump channel, Sibley will leave this one in his sleep. Does the same while he is awake too.
Comes around slightly slower and on off, Sibley pushes this one to the cover-point region. 'No run' is the early call from Dom. Also, no ball called for overstepping.
Around off on a length, tucked to the leg side.
Slightly closer to the off pole on a good length, but still not enough to trouble Dom who raises his willow and lets this one through to Pant.

BEAUTYYY! A jaffa to end with from Sharma. A wry smile on his face after this delivery. On a good length and around off, straightens a touch after hitting the deck as Dom looks to block this one out. Misses and the ball whizzes past the outside edge to Pant.
Gets his bat down and defends this one to mid-wicket.
Drags his length back and bowls a bumper on middle and leg, Burns sits under this one. 'BOWLING, JASSSSSI', is that the Indian players are chattering around, to show their support to Bumrah.
Rory has just watchfully blocked this out.
Slightly behind that good length area, closer to off, Burns tucks this one but finds the fielder stationed at square leg.
Bowls a full toss around off, Burns works this one towards Gill at mid on.
A dot to end and Bumrah gets a maiden. On a length and around off, Rory keeps it out.
On a length and around off, Dom pushes this one to point. There is a bit of yes-no regarding the single but nothing results of it.
On a good length and outside off, DS blocks.
On middle, clipped to the fielder present at short mid-wicket.
Sibley tucks this one to the short mid-wicket fielder yet again.
Outside off, left alone this time around by Dom.
On a good length and on off, Sibley pushes this one to the left of the mid on fielder. Back-to-back maidens for the Indians.
Floated on middle, Burns prods forward looking to block this one but the ball takes the inner half of the blade and goes through square leg for a single.

FOUR! First boundary for the English Lions and SIbley is the one who supplies this one. Short and wide outside off, Sibley goes on his back foot and slaps this one through backward point to fetch a boundary.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.
On off, tucked to the leg side yet again.
Flat and around off, spins back in after hitting the deck slightly, Sibley goes on his back foot and clips this one through square leg for one more run.
Flighted on middle, Burns defends this one out. 6 runs off Ashwin's first over.
Length and around off, Sibley pushes this one to covers.
Gets his bat down and blocks this one to the mid on region.
On a length and around off, Dom pushes this one to the cover region again. Sibley raises his blade and yells a loud 'NO RUN, NO RUNNNN' to Rory.
Bumper on middle, Dom ducks under this one well.
On a good length and on middle, enough for Dom to flick it through square leg for a single.

Bit of hesitation for the single but they get it in the end. On a length and on off, Burns tucks this one to square leg and the batters have a bit of yes-no again. But they go for it and complete it in the end. 2 off this over. A steady start by England so far.
Tossed up and around off, Rory keeps it out.
Comfortable couple this time. On middle, Burns goes back slightly and clips this one through square leg. Comes back for the second run as well.
Loopy on off, Rory comes on his front foot and blocks.
Bowls this around leg, spins back in slightly as Burns comes forward and fends this one out.
Outside off, Burns is aware of his off pole as he lets this one through.
On middle, kept out.
EDGY. On a good length and around off, Sibley looks to defend this one but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes through the slip cordon for one run.
Bumrah slips this one down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses this one.

Overthrows and a single. On a length and on off, Rory pushes this one to covers and looks for the single. Dom sends him back. Nadeem runs in and takes the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses as Rory puts in a dive. There is no one backing up and so the batters can take on run there.

Good length and on middle, clipped to the deep square leg region where Nadeem runs to his right and looks to stop this one and does so with his boot. He pushes the ball out of play and the batters take three. The umpires want to confirm this and concur with the third umpire. Replays roll in and it is seen that it is a clean save. Three runs.
Outside off, left alone.
Rory defends this one solidly off the front foot.
Flighted around off, Dom keeps this one out.
Slightly short and on leg, tucked to square leg this time.
Dom comes on the front foot and keeps this one out.
On middle, clipped to the leg side.
Tossed up and on middle, DS fends this one out.
EDGY SINGLE. Sibley takes one on the last ball. Flighted on off, Sibley looks to tuck this one to the leg side but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards point for one run.
Fuller on off and middle, Sibley flicks it away from short mid-wicket for a single.
Full on off, Burns defends it to mid off.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Full around off, Burns looks to play it towards mid on. The ball goes off the outer half of his bat through point for a single. Nadeem does well to stop the ball.
Nicely defended! Full outside off, Sibley gets on his front foot and blocks it.

Excellent running! Fullish ball on off and middle. Sibley gently pushes it to the left of mid on. The batters call for a quick run. Ishant charges to the ball and sends a wild throw at the keeper's end. Pant behind the stumps does well to stop it.
Flighted on off, Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket with the spin.

FOUR! Good shot! Sibley is looking good out in the middle. Floated delivery on middle and leg, Sibley gets on his front foot and flicks it through mid-wicket. Rohit Sharma gives it a chase and puts in a slide too but the ball beats him to the fence.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it off his back foot.
Tossed up on the stumps, Sibley defends it.
Tossed up on middle, Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
Good length ball around off, Burns flicks it straight to the man at catching short mid-wicket.
Length ball around off, Burns tucks it to square leg. He looks for a run but Sibley is quick to turn him down.
Good length delivery around off, Burns taps it to point.
On middle and off, Burns shuffles in his trademark style and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball on middle and off, Sibley flicks it to the on side and gets a single.

Almost a Bumrah special. He bowls a dipping low full toss around off, Burns manages to push it to mid off for a single. NO BALL! It has been caught by the T.V. umpire. Second no ball of the day. One by Ishant and now by Bumrah.
Beauty to end the over. Bumrah bowls this on a good length area around off. Sibley looks to defend but the ball shapes away and beats the outside edge of Sibley's bat.
Floated on off, Burns blocks it.

Good running and also good fielding! Floated on off, Burns comes down the track and hits it to the right of mid off. He takes off for a quick run. Shahbaz Nadeem gets to the ball and scores a direct-hit but Burns is well in.
Tossed up on the stumps, Sibley blocks it.
Flighted on middle, Sibley tucks it to the on side with the spin.
Floated on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Shortish on the stumps, Sibley knocks it to the on side.
On off, blocked to mid-wicket.
Short and on middle, Burns gets on his knees and sweeps this one to the deep mid-wicket region and the fielder giving it chase does well to pull it back before the ropes. Three runs.
Flighted on off, Dom looks to block this one but the ball takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Shorter and outside off, slapped to covers.
Dom Sibley has just watchfully blocked this out.

FOUR! Sibley plays this one very well. Width on offer and he pounces. This one is fractionally short and also outside off, Sibley camps back and slaps this one through the point region to fetch the boundary.
Comes on the front foot and blocks.
Another solid defense offered by Burns to this one.
Flatter and outside off, Burns slaps this one through the cover region and Bumrah does well to chase this one down and pull it back before the ropes. Three this time.
On middle, tucked to short leg.
Flighted and on leg, flicked to short leg.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Angled into the pads, Burns works it through square leg for one.
Well bowled! Slows it up, it is outside off, draws the batter into playing at it. Sibley pushes it to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Short and around off, pushed to the cover region.
On middle, defended back by Dom.
Flighted on off, Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
50 up for England. Flighted on middle, clipped to the square leg region for a couple of runs.
Floated on the stumps, Burns defends it.
Flighted on off, Burns gets on his front foot and defends it.
Tossed up on off, Burns is happy to watchfully negotiate it.
Nadeem gives this one air around off. Sibley uses his tall frame as he leans forward and blocks it.
Shorter on off, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Flighted around off, Sibley defends it to point.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
Floated outside off, Sibley tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Single to end the over! Nadeem floats the last ball on the pads. Sibley is happy to turn it around to mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
Tossed up on middle, Sibley plays it short mid-wicket.
Shouts of catch it but it is away from the man at leg gully. On the pads, Sibley flicks it uppishly but away from Gill at leg gully.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley taps it to cover for a single.

FOUR! Ashwin is not finding it as easy as he would have hoped for coming back to India. Nicely played shot from Burns! Flighted delivery around off, Burns takes a big stride forward and sweeps it fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Flighted on the stumps, Burns keeps it out.
On off, kept out by RB.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley defends it.
On middle, Sibley turns it to short square leg.
Flighted on off, Sibley leans forward and defends it.
Tossed up around off, Sibley defends it to point.
Flighted on middle, Sibley keeps it out.
NO BALL! Nadeem oversteps and that is criminal if you are a spinner. Floated around off, Sibley pushes it to cover.
Arm ball to finish the over. It is just outside off, Sibley taps it onto the ground. Another No Ball called for overstepping.
Flighted around off, kept out.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Brilliant use of the feet from Burns! Rory comes down the track and hits it wide of mid on against the spin for a boundary.
Shorter on off, Burns defends it.
Tossed up on middle, Burns blocks it.
Flighted on off, Burns blocks it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ashwin gets the breakthrough and the budding, gritty opening stand has been broken. The bigger question is where has this shot come from, Rory Burns and was it even necessary in the first place? This is a Christmas gift for Ashwin from Burns which has come super early. Ashwin comes over the wicket for the southpaw and bowls a floated delivery on middle. Burns brings out the reverse sweep. The ball bounces a tad extra, kisses his glove and lobs around the stump. Easy catch for Pant who will not drop these even in his sleep. Jubilation for Ashwin and co. Disappointment for Burns.
Floated on the stumps, Lawrence starts his innings with a front foot defense.
Tossed up on middle, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Flighted on off, Sibley blocks it.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley defends it.
On the stumps, kept out by Sibley.
Nadeem flights one on off. Sibley looks to defend and does so off the outer half of his bat.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley watchfully blocks it.
Good length ball outside off from Bumrah to start his new spell. Lawrence leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Dan Lawrence defends it with a straight bat.
Fuller and targetting the stumps. Lawrence defends it.

OUT! LBW! As plumb as it gets! Bumrah strikes for the first time in his Test career in India. This is a typical Bumrah delivery. Credit to Kohli as well. He has done his homework. Lawrence is a good player of spin and he easily could have continued with Ashwin after the spinner got a wicket but he introduced Bumrah and his strike bowler gives him the breakthrough. Fuller delivery pitching around off and jagging back in at pace. Lawrence looks to flick but is too late to get his bat down and the ball hits him on the backpad. Bumrah knows he has his man but puts in the mandatory appeal. The umpire has no qualms in raising the finger. Lawrence has a word with Sibley but he gets no support from him for the review. Good call because it looked plumb and the Ball Tracker later on proves it.
Root is up and running straight away! Good length ball around off, Root taps it through point and gets off the mark with a single.
Bumrah targets the stumps, Lawrence defends it with a straight bat.

In the air but thankfully for Root it is in the gap. Floated on off, Root looks to play it on the leg side. There is some turn and bounce for Ashwin. It takes the edge and flies through cover in the vacant region. Two taken.
Floated on off, Root blocks it.
Short around off, Root blocks it.

NOT OUT! Frantic but in the end the England Test skipper is safe. A run out here would be nothing but disastrous for England especially right before Lunch. Short on off, Root turns it to square leg and takes a single. There is a slight hesitation but they go for it. The fielder scores a direct hit at the bowler's end.The umpire takes it upstairs and replay shows it is not a direct hit but Ashwin deflected the ball onto the stumps. Anyway, Root is well inside the crease and safe.
Floated on off, Sibley lunges and blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Sibley manages to keep it out. That will be the final ball of the session. Lunch on Day 1!
Starts off with a good length delivery just outside the off pole, Root is aware of where his sticks are as he lets this one through to the keeper.
Length and around off, Root taps this one towards the cover-point region. They look for the single but then do not go for it.
Outside off on a good length, stays a touch low as well, Root leaves it.
Length and on off, Root pushes this one to mid on.
Gets his bat down and blocks this one to the leg side.
One run to end the over. On a length and around the off pole, Joe pushes this one through point and collects a single. Retains the strike for the next over.
Flighted around off, Root prods forward and keeps this one out.
Tossed up and around off, Root again comes ahead and blocks. 'Beautiful bowling, Ashwinnnn', says Virat Kohli, to appreciate his bowler.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Tossed up and around off, Root pushes this one to the cover region for a single.
On off, blocked by Dom.
Loopy and around off again, Sibley tucks this one to mid-wicket.
Bowls this one with the angle around the off pole, Root defends.
Gets his bat down and blocks this one to the mid off region.
Fires in a fuller ball on the middle pole, Root tucks this one but finds the square leg fielder.
Good length and around off, Joe taps this one towards the fielder present at gully.
Same sort of delivery as the last ball, Root plays the same kind of stroke. Finds the man there again.

Bumrah fires in a short ball down the leg side, Root just lets it be. Pant does well to move to his left and stop this one. Called a wide first but then called as a no ball as the third umpire passes on the message.
On off, played to the mid on region.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted on middle, Sibley clips this one nicely through the mid-wicket region and the batters come back for the double.
On middle, clipped to the short leg fielder.
Prods on his front foot this time to defend solidly, does Dom.
Another solid block offered by Sibley.
Loopy around off, Dom pushes this to point. 2 runs off this over.
Good running between the wickets by these two. On a good length and on middle, Root clips this one through square leg. The batters do well to come back for the double.
Fires this one with the angle on the off stump, Root shuffles slightly and works this to short mid-wicket.
An exact replica of what happened on the last ball. Root finds the short mid-wicket again.
Since this is bowled closer to outside the off pole, Root defends it towards the cover region now.

Delightfully played by the skipper, Bumrah goes for a fuller shot and on middle, Root is able to flick this one through the mid-wicket region. By the time, Gill can run in and stop the ball, three runs are taken.
Dom finds the mid-wicket fielder with his flick this time. 5 off this one.
Root shows off his back foot defense this time around.
Flighted and outside off, Root is about to leave this one but decides to play it at the last minute. Misses and Pant collects.
Flighted and on off, Root looks for the flick away and the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes to the off side.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Joe Root has just watchfully blocked this out as well.
Goes on the back foot and gets his bat across to fend this one out. The skipper does that successfully to see off this Ashwin over.
Slightly behind the good length and around the off pole, Dom tucks this to short mid-wicket.
Blocks this one to the leg side, does Sibley.
Around off on a length, Sibley works this one to the gully region.
Good length and on off, Sibley finds the Indian skipper, Kohli at short mid-wicket again.
On the middle pole on a fuller length, slight inward movement noticed as Dibley whips this one to deep mid-wicket where Gill collects this one. Just the single.
Length and outside off, nipping into the right-hander after hitting the deck as Root covers his sticks and the ball goes to Pant. A wry smile on Root's face after this one.
Ohhh...what a beauty! Ashwin comes 'round the wicket and floats this one up around the off pole, Sibley comes ahead looking to block but he misses his defensive push completely.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Shortish and outside off, Dom camps back and looks to slash at this one but he does not connect bat with ball.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Screams of 'catch it' but it goes through the fielders there. Flighted and on middle, Sibley comes forward and flicks this one uppishly through the square leg region for a single.
On middle, blocked out.
Back of a length and on middle, Dom clips this one to the left of the deep square leg fielder for a single. Also, called as No Ball as Ishant had overstepped.
Back of a length and outside off, Root looks to slash this one away but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the left of Pant.
The English skipper blocks this one nicely to the Indian skipper at the short mid-wicket region.
Too straight and also moving into the right-hander, Root looks to flick but misses and the ball takes the pads and goes to Pant again.
Length and outside off, tapped to point.

An excited appeal for lbw but turned down by the umpire. A back of a length ball around off, it jags back in after hitting the deck and goes onto hit Root's pads as he misses his flick away. A loud appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Must have been high and also going down leg. Kohli and Ishant ask Pant what he thinks and he says that they probably should not take the review on this one.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Short and on off, Sibley works this to mid-wicket.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket again.
Floated on middle, flicked to short leg.
Loopy and on leg, clipped to deep square leg where Sundar stops this one well.
Blocks this one solidly off the front foot.
Comes down the track slightly and flicks this one to deep square leg again. Maiden by Ashwin.
Good length and around off, Root is solid in his defense.

EDGED...SHORT! Great bowling by Ishant. Bowls a good length ball around off, nips away slightly as Root plays this one with soft hands. It takes the outside edge and goes to Rohit on the bounce at first slip. Smart work by Joe to play it with soft hands and that is why this one did not carry to the slip.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Length and on off, worked to the leg side.
Slowish good length ball around off, Root blocks this one out towards the off side.
Fuller and on off, Root clips this one to deep mid-wicket.
Flighted and on off, blocked. Kohli is heard saying 'BAHUT ACCHE ASHHH', which means 'Very good, Ash'.
FOUR! Sibley releases some pressure now for the visitors. Flighted and on middle, Sibley flicks this one through the mid-wicket region and the ball runs away to the ropes.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, left alone by Dom.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Floated and on off, Dom keeps this one out nicely. 4 runs off this over, courtesy Dom.
Flighted on off, Root keeps this one out.
Short and around off, pushed to the off side.
Down the leg side, JR misses his flick and it bounces a tad bit more than what Pant anticipated as he spills this one.
On off, pushed to covers.
Tucked to square leg with soft hands by the skipper.
Loopy and around off, Root pushes this one to covers for a quick run.
Floats this one up around off, Root prods forward and keeps it out.
FOUR! Classy stroke from Root, who welcomes Sundar into the game with a boundary. Flighted and around off, Root moves away and creams this one through the cover region to find the fence.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
On off, kept out.
Loopy and on middle, Root gets low and brings out the broom. Sweeps this one to the square leg region for a single.
Full and floated on middle, flicked to mid-wicket. 5 runs off Sundar's first over of the game.
Darted full on off, Root keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up around off, Root leans forward and defends it.
Deft touch! Short around off, Root dabs it towards third man. He looks for two but decides against it. Good call as it would have been very dangerous.
Flighted on off, Sibley defends it off his front foot.
Tossed up on off, Sibley defends it to the right of the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Root defends it off the outer half of his bat to point.
Flatter on middle and leg, Root defends it to the leg side.
Tossed up around off, Root leans forward and blocks it.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Root brings out the reverse sweep and unlike Burns, he plays it with perfection. Tossed up outside off, Root picks the right length and the right ball to play the shot. He hits it behind point for a boundary.
Floated on off, Root goes back to watchfully defending it.
On the stumps, the England skipper carefully defends it.
Tossed up around off, Sibley strides forward and defends it.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Excellent shot! He uses his feet to perfection there. Tossed up on off and middle, Sibley puts on his dancing shoes and plays it with a straight bat through the cow corner region for a boundary. 100 up for England as well.
Tossed up around off, Sibley goes back to defending.
Shorter on middle and leg. Sibley flicks it onto the ground. It hits Gill's pad at short leg.
Floated on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Shorter around off, Root tucks it to the on side.
Around the pads. Root glances it to fine leg and gets to the other end. Runs starting to come frequently now for this pair.
Darted full on middle and leg. Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
This time Sibley flicks it with softer hands and wide of Rohit Sharma at mid-wicket for one.
Swept hard but there is a man at deep backward square leg. On the pads, Root sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Good take from Pant! Pitched outside leg, Sibley leaves it alone. There is some extra bounce off the surface on this one. Pant takes it well as that was not an easy take.

Beautifully played! Short around off, Root punches it through point. Sundar misfields and there is a yes-no for the second and they opt against it. Good call, they will not want to risk a wicket in chasing a run.
Tossed up on the stumps, Sibley blocks it.
On the stumps, kept out.
Flighted on off, Sibley blocks it.
Tossed up around off, Sibley comes down the track and defends it.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
Darted fuller on middle and leg. Root reverse sweeps it to backward point for a single.
Floated on middle, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket and shouts an audible no.
Good ball! Washington gives this a lot of air on middle and leg. Sibley looks to flick but closes the face of the bat early. The ball goes to point off the leading edge.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.

FOUR! Uppish but safe! Floated on middle, Sibley brings out an aggressive sweep. There is a shout of catch it as it goes uppishly but it well away from short leg and mid-wicket. Sibley finds the gap and gets a boundary. Moves to 44 with that.
Tossed up on off, Sibley blocks it.
Flighted outside off, Root shoulders arms to it. Pant likes the pace at which this is bowled as he says it in Hindi to Nadeem.
FOUR! Brings up the 50-run stand. Tossed up fuller around off, Root strides forward and sweeps it in front of square for a boundary.
Flighted on off, Root blocks it.
Tossed up on middle, Root defends it.
Shahbaz Nadeem gives this a bit of air on middle. Root defends it off the inner half of his bat.
NO BALL! Another one from Nadeem and he needs to sort these out now. Short on middle, Root flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Excellent from Sibley. Just two away now from what will be a very good and gritty fifty if he gets there. Flighted on middle, Sibley uses his wrists and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Nicely bowled. Floated around off, Root defends it towards point.
Short around leg, Root dabs it to the leg side.
Shorter on off, Root defends it off his back foot.
Falls just short of leg slip! On the pads, Root flicks it behind on the leg side. There is a leg slip for this shot but unluckily for Kohli and co. it falls short of the fielder there.
On the pads, Root flicks it in front of the crease on the leg side and gets a single.
On the pads, Sibley blocks it.
On a good length and on middle, clipped to the square leg region for a single.
Length and around off, Sibley blocks this one out.
Good length and on off, Sibley pushes this one to the mid on region.
Outside off on a good length, way too outside the off pole for Dom to be to worried about having to play at this. Lets it be.
Angles in a length delivery around off, Dom blocks this one out.
On the pads this time, Sibley tickles this one to the fine leg region for one. Moves onto 49 with this one. Just one run away from his half-century.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it off his back foot.

FIFTY FOR SIBLEY! This has been a gritty knock from the English opener. A real impressive innings from Sibley. He has shown heart and courage today. Shorter on off, Sibley punches it through covers and gets a brace to bring up his fifty. It has been a well-composed innings from him/. He raises his bat as his teammates applaud his effort. He knows the job is not done though and he will look to convert this into a hundred.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Sibley defends it.
Darted around the pads, Dom Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Floated on midddle, Sibley blocks it.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it.
Length delivery angling in on middle. Root flicks it using the angle behind square on the leg side for one.
NO BALL! On off, Sibley blocks it. It is another no ball as Bumrah has overstepped.
Length ball on off, Sibley defends it.
Edged but does not carry! Leg cutter on off, Sibley looks to defend but gets an outside edge which does not carry to Rohit Sharma at first slip.
Wow! This is crispy from Bumrah! A leg cutter is followed by a pacy yorker on middle. Sibley does really well to get his bat down in time.
On the pads, Sibley defends it to the leg side.
Floated on off, Root sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Shorter around the pad, Sibley tucks it to the on side.
Flighted on the stumps, Sibley defends it.
Flights one on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Sibley keeps it out.

In the air but off the pad. Floated outside off, Sibley looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his pad and lobs to leg slip, who takes the catch. There is a muted appeal but nothing from the umpire.

Appeal for LBW but turned down by the umpire. Seems like it is going down leg and hence Kohli has opted to not review it. Slower delivery on middle and leg. Root looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad. There is an appeal but the umpire is not interested. Kohli, Bumrah and Pant have a chat but the latter does not seem too keen and the Indian skipper does not review it. Good call not to review it as Ball Tracker shows it to be going down leg later on.
Full on the pads, Root flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Short ball from Bumrah! The effort ball. Sibley ducks under it.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to the leg side.
Angled into middle, Sibley flicks but to mid-wicket.
Good running! Fuller around off, Sibley pushes it to the right of mid off and takes a quick single to keep the strike.
Short and spinning in around off. Sibley knocks it to mid off for a single.
Shorter on off, Root defends it.
Another one which is short on off, Root gets on his back foot and defends it.
FOUR! First poor ball from Ashwin and Root is quick to punish it. Short around off, too short and slightly wider from off pole. Root pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! This time through the off side. Too short, very wide, and Root is in too good a form to miss out on it. He gets on his back foot and punches it through covers. There is a huge gap there and the England Test skipper hits it in that gap for a boundary. Back-to-back poor deliveries from Ashwin. You seldom see that.  Is it the sign of the spinner being tired?
Shorter on the pads, Root dabs in onto the ground in front of short leg.
Length ball around off, Sibley blocks it.
Keeps a bit low. Good length ball on off, it comes in a bit with the angle and keeps low. Sibley adjusts to the bounce in the eleventh hour and manages to get bat on ball.
Fuller around off, Sibley gets on his front foot and defends it. No problem with the bounce this time around.
Full around off, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Beauty! Ishant has been brilliant today. Reverse swing on offer for him. Fuller outside off, it comes back in. Sibley looks to defend but is a bit late and luckily does not get any bat on it.

NO BALL! This one goes the other way around. Outside off on a length. Sibley does well as he keeps his eyes on the ball and leaves it alone. Oh, dear! Another no ball from India. They have been poor with their discipline. Not something you usually associate with this Kohli-led side.
Length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Flighted on off, Root defends it.
Tossed up around off, Root leans forward and blocks it.
Floated on off, Root whips it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, Root defends it to the leg side.
Flighted on middle, Root sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
Last ball of the session, and Sibley negotiates it. Floated on off and middle, Sibley gets on his front foot and dabs it onto the ground. Tea on Day 1!

EDGE..DOES NOT CARRY! This one does not carry to Pant. It was an under edge though. On a good length and outside off, Root looks to push this one to the off side but the ball stays low and takes the under edge and goes to Pant on a bounce.
Length and outside off, pushed to covers.

EDGED...DOES NOT CARRY AGAIN! Takes the outside edge this time. On a length and outside off, moving away from the right-hander, the ball takes the outside edge off Root's tentative poke as goes to the right of Pant and the ball bounces just before he could take it and goes into his gloves.
Back of a length and on middle, clipped to the leg side.
Fuller and on middle, Root clips this one to the deep square leg region for one run.
Defends this one solidly to the mid-wicket region. A good over to start with by Sharma.
Short and around off, Root punches this one to the cover region.
Prods on the front foot and blocks.
Flatter and outside off, slapped to the cover region again. No run though.
Too short and on off, Joe pulls this one to the deep mid-wicket region towards Ishant. Takes a single.
Gives it air and lands it on middle and leg, Dom tucks this one to the on side for one more run.

FIFTY FOR JOE ROOT! His 50th half-century and in his 100th Test game, he has put up a good show once again. The English skipper seems to have carried forward his form from the Sri Lankan series and he is looking very solid out there. He will though want to continue on. Shortish and outside off, Root slaps this one through point and even though Sundar gives it chase, he tries to stop this one but fumbles and lets the ball trickle through to the ropes.
On middle, flicked to the on side for a single.
Bumper outside off, Root just lets this one though to the keeper.
NO BALL! Another one from India. Short ball around the body, Root pulls it behind square leg for a couple.
Play and a miss! Good length ball around off, Root has a poke at it. The ball though shapes away and beats the outside edge of Root's willow.
Lenght ball on off, Root defends it with a straight bat.
Good shot! Length ball around off, Root punches it through cover for a couple.
Full on off, Root flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Short and spinning away. Sibley punches it to cover.
Flighted outside off, Sibley pushes it to cover.
Floated on off and middle, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Too short, too wide, and rightfully punished! Short and spinning away from outside off. Sibley cuts it behind point for a boundary.
Tossed up outside off, Sibley gets on his front foot and defends it.
Around the pad, Sibley turns it to square leg.
Full on off and middle, Root flicks it to the right of deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length delivery around off, Root defends it with a straight bat.
Reverse swing where the ball comes in. It is outside off, Sibley is aware of his off pole and shoulders arms to it.
This one shapes away a bit. Sibley once again calmly leaves it alone.
Fuller around off, Sibley defends it.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley flicks it behind square on the leg side and keeps the strike.
Floated on off, Sibley gets on his front foot and blocks it.
Good leave! Flighted outside off, the ball turns in a bit. Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Down the leg side. Sibley looks to turn it on the on side but misses. Pant appeals but no one else is interested.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
Good fielding from Pujara. On the pads, Sibley flicks it to the right of mid-wicket. Pujara there dives and saves runs for his side.
Gives this air on off, Sibley carefully blocks it.
Good length ball outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Fuller around off, Root defends it by bending his back.
Good shot but straight to the fielder. Length ball around off, Root punches it off the middle of the bat but straight to cover.

FOUR! Glorious! Close your eyes and imagine a beautiful cover drive, that is what has Root has played. Fuller ball outside off, not a half volley by any means. Root shows great balance as he goes on his front foot. The England Test skipper then shows crispy timing and drives it through cover for a boundary. Elegant way to bring up the 100-run stand. This has been a very good stand between the England skipper and the English opener.
Bumrah pulls his length back a bit and Root calmly defends it.
Around off, Root defends it to get through the over.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted on middle, kept out.
Short and on off, Dom keeps this one out as well.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket. They think about the single but then decide not to go for it in the end.
FOUR! Another beautiful boundary by Sibley. His 9th one of the game. Tossed up and on middle, Dom whips this one through the mid-wicket region and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Comes down the track and pushes this one to the left of mid on. They want the single but seeing that the fielder has stopped this one. They opt against it.
Good length ball around off, Root drives it beautifully but straight to the man at cover.
Yorker. Bumrah special this. Root does well to jam it out.
Short ball around middle, Root pulls it away from deep mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Fuller around off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Root sways away from it.
Full and coming back in. Root looks to defend but the ball comes in a little extra. It goes behind square leg off the inner half of his bat for a single.
Short on off, Root defends it off the back foot.
Floated on middle, Root sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Floated on off, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot with a straight bat.
On the stumps, kept out.
Floated on off, Sibley keeps it out.
FOUR! Not the kind if welcome Washington Sundar would have wanted. A gift from Sundar as he bowls one down the leg side. Root sweeps it fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Root defends it off his front foot.
Floated on off, Root keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Root leans forward and defends it.
Another sweep from Root! This is played through square leg for a couple.
Floated on off, Root defends it off his front foot.
Floated around off, Sibley pushes it to Rohit Sharma at cover.
Tossed up outside off, Sibley taps it to point.
Flighted on off, Sibley comes down the track and pushes it to cover.
Arm ball outside off. Sibley picks it up and leaves it alone.
Uppish but safe! Floated on off, Sibley drives it uppshly but it falls short of Kohli at short extra cover.
Arm ball again outside off. It is bowled slower through the air. Sibley leaves it alone.
Flighted on off, pushed to the mid on region.
Quick run this time. Flighted around off, Root looks to push this one away but the ball takes the inside edge, hits the pads and goes to the off side for a quick run.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Blocks this one solidly off the front foot.
Loopy and on off, Dom keeps this one out.
Another solid front foot defense shown by Sibley this time.
Shortish and outside off, Root slaps this one to the point region.

In the air...safe! Root looks to play the sweep but it takes the top edge this time. Flighted on off, Root sweeps but the top edge takes the ball aierally towards the mid-wicket region for a couple of runs.
Outside off, cut away to point.
FOUR! Root has absolutely nailed that one! Flighted around off, Root gets on his knees and brings out the broom. Sweeps this one fine towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Goes on his back foot this time around and fends it out.
Full and tossed up and on leg, Joe tucks this one towards square leg for a quick run. 7 runs off this over.
Flighted and on middle, eased through the mid on region for a single.
Shortish and around off, Dom defends this one towards the leg side.
Sibley shows off his front foot defense, which is very solid.
Flighted and around the off pole, Dom whips this one through mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Full and on middle, Root keeps this one out.
Root goes on his back foot and whips this one through the mid-wicket region for a single.
FOUR! Root plays this shot so well. He moves onto 84 as well. Great control. Flighted on middle, Root switches his stance and powers this one through the backward point region and into the ropes.
On off, kept out.
On middle and leg, Root just pads this one away to the leg side.
Short and on the leg pole, flicked to the leg side again.
Tossed up and on leg now, Root works this one to the short fine leg region for a quick single. That came off the toe end of the bat as well.
Tossed up and on middle and leg, Dom tucks this one to square leg. Gets to the other end this time. Oh no! Another no ball for overstepping.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! A wayward throw and extra runs for England. Short and on off, Root punches this one to the cover region and the fielder there collects the ball. He sees Sibley out of the crease and tries to hit bullseye but he misses. There is no one backing up and the ball runs away to the deep mid-wicket ropes.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Shortish and on middle, he pushes it with a straight bat towards mid-wicket again.
Flighted on middle, DS looks to sweep this one but he finds the leg slip fielder.
On the middle pole, flatter as well, Dom goes on the back foot and whips this one through square leg for one more run. 200 up for England.

FOUR! Wonderful placement. Root escorts this one to the boundary now. Into the 90s now, is Root. Floats it up and lands it on middle, Root whips this one nicely through mid-wicket and the ball wins the race to the ropes.
On off, pushed to the mid off region for a quick run.
Shortish and around off, pushed to the cover region.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted on middle, Root blocks coming on his front foot.

FOUR! Played it so late and the ball wins the race to the ropes again. Root moves onto 98 now. Short and around off, Root waits and waits and waits and then guides this one through the short third man region into the ropes in the deep.
Joe Root has just watchfully blocked this out.
On middle, blocked to the leg side this time.
Tossed up and on middle, pushed away to the leg side.

FOUR! Swept away and swept away very nicely. This also brings up the 150-run partnership between these two. Tossed up and around leg, Sibley gets down on his knees and sweeps this one fine to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

An appeal for lbw but nothing from the umpire. Floats this one up around leg and middle, Dom gets down and looks to sweep again but misses it and gets rapped on the pads. A loud appeal but no says the umpire. Was pitching outside leg this one.
Dom defends this one solidly off the front foot.
Tosses it up and lands it on leg, DS clips this one to square leg for one more run.
Flighted on off, pushed to the short cover fielder.
FOUR! Too short and too wide for Sibley to not do have a go at this. Dom sends this one packing to the ropes. Shortish and outside off, slashed away to the deep point region for a boundary.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Tossed up and on off, DS comes on the front foot and defends solidly.
Another solid defense offered to this one by Dom.
Outside off, Sibley works this one to the fielder present at covers.
Flighted and on off, Root works this one to the mid off region and picks up a single. Wanted two but it was not possible to do so. He moves onto 99 now.
The batsman, Dom Sibley has just blocked that from his crease.
Flighted and on middle and leg, Sibley works this with soft hands towards the deep square leg region for a couple of runs.

FOUR! Another sweep and another boundary! Gill misfields and lets this one through. Flighted and on middle, Sibley gets on his knees and sweeps this one to the deep square leg region and Gill misfields and lets this one through to the ropes.
On the pads, flicked to fine leg for one.

HUNDRED FOR JOE ROOT! His 3rd in as many Tests. What a fantastic knock this has been from the England skipper. Playing his 100th Test and he has doubled his joy by scoring a fantastic ton. All his teammates are up on their feet, applauding their skipper who has led from the front. The England Test skipper was unable to score a single century in 2020 but 2 months into 2021 he has his third. What a player! An absolute joy to watch. In a country where many England legends have struggled he has blossomed like a beautiful flower. Root pumps his fist in the air, removes his helmet, kisses it and soaks in all the applause. A phenomenal batsman in phenomenal form. On the pads, Root flicks it away behind square on the leg side and gets to his 20th Test ton. Indian skipper, Virat Kohli, applauds his counterpart as well and shows great sportsman spirit as this has been a top-class innings.
Floated and on off, Root keeps this one out.
On middle, Joe gets on his knees and sweeps this one to the deep square leg region for one run.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
On the pads, flicked to the leg side.
Flicked away to the leg side again by Dom. Pant still trying his best to keep the morale up by cheering the players on.
Floated on off, Sibley comes down the track looking to flick this one away. But misses and gets rapped on the pads. A stifled appeal and the umpire says no. Just one run off this over.
Brings out the broom again as this full and floated ball on middle is swept away to fine leg for a brace.

FOUR. That's just a gentle push from Root and he still fetches a boundary. Tosses it up and lands it just around off, Root pushes this one nicely through the mid off region and the ball runs away to the ropes.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.
Shortish and around off, JR pushes this one through point for a single.
Dom blocks this one after going on his back foot this time.
Flighted and on off, Dom tucks this one to mid-wicket.
Flighted and on middle, Root skips down the track and works this one to the mid on region for a single.

FOUR LEG BYES. Lucky for England and Sibley. Nothing seems to be going India's way. Flighted and on the pads, Sibley looks to block this one out but the ball takes the pad and lobs over the leg slip fielder and into the ropes at fine leg.
Short and on off, pushed to the mid-wicket region.
Shortish and outside off now, DS punches this one off the back foot through the cover region for a brace.
On off, kept out.
Dom Sibley has just blocked that from his crease.
Outside off on a good length, Root shoulders arms to this one.
Ishant slips this one down the leg side as Root misses his tuck away to the leg side.

FOUR! Oh wow! Handsomely driven. Looking at that cover drive could make a grown man cry. Beautiful. On a good length and outside off, Root leans into this one and Root creams his drive through the cover region and into the ropes.
Good length and around off again, Joe drives this one to the left of mid on and the fielder does well to move that way and stop it.
Changes it up now, does Root. Pushes this one to the fielder at mid off this time around.
Fullish and on the pads, Root clips this one to the left of the fine leg fielder for a single. 5 off the first over with the new ball for Ishant.
Length ball on middle and off. Root flicks it in front of square on the leg side for a brace.
Full around off, Root pushes it to cover.
That is a beauty! Good length ball, in the channel of uncertainty around off. Root has a poke at it but the ball moves away and fizzes past the outside edge.

Another beauty! The previous one shaped away as this one just straightened after pitching. Again it is pitched in the channel of uncertainty around off. Root looks to defend thinking it to come in with the angle. The ball though goes straight past the outside edge.
Length ball outside off, Root offers a confident leave this time.
Full outside off, Root pushes it to cover.
Length delivery outside off, Sibley has no interest in playing that.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley lets it carry to the keeper.
Back of a length ball outside off. Sibley has no qualms letting that go.
Good length ball on the fourth stump line. Sibley opens the gate and lets the ball go through that gate to the keeper.
Outside off, Sibley offers no shot.
Full outside off, Sibley leans on the front foot and offers a solid block.
Angles in a length ball close to off, Root defends it back with a loose bottom hand.
This one probably stays a bit low! Bumrah hurls in a length ball around off, Root keeps his eyes glued to the delivery and defends it with a dead bat.
Back of a length and around off, JR taps this one towards point.
Shortish and around off, Root hooks this one to the deep square leg region. Picks up a single and also brings up the 250 for England.
Gets his bat across and blocks this one solidly.
Outside off, left alone.
Short of a length and outside off, Root slaps this one to the point region for a single.
Back of a length and around off, Sibley pushes this one to the mid on region.
Fuller and around the off pole, Dom gets on his front foot and offers a very solid defense to this one.
Dom Sibley just pushes this good length delivery to the cover region this time.
Fuller again and just around the off stump, Sibley blocks.
Gets his bat across and offers yet another solid defense to the last ball of the over.
Short on the pads, Root flicks it on the bounce to short leg.
Floated on off, Root looks to defend but the ball goes towards point off the outer half of his bat for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball which is given some air on off. Sibley looks to defend but the ball spins in and goes between short leg and leg slip off the inner half of his bat for a single.
Flighted on off, Root drives it through covers for a couple.

SIX! Boom! Root finishes the over with a biggie. That will irk Ashwin for sure. Tossed up ball on off and middle, Root brings out the slog sweep and smokes it over mid-wicket for a biggie. The England skipper is struggling with cramp but he is not letting that affect his batting much.
Down the leg side. Sibley does not tease that.
Full on off, Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Sibley defends it with a dead bat.
Textbook front foot defense this from Sibley. Fuller around off, Sibley gets on his front foot and defends it onto the ground.
Full around off, Sibley pushes it to cover.
Short around off, Root punches it through cover-point and gets a single.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Floated on off, Root blocks it.
Flighted on off, Root defends it.
Tossed up around off, Root goes on his back foot and keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Root goes on his back foot and taps it onto the ground.
On the fourth stump line, Sibley leaves it alone.
Good length ball around off, Sibley blocks it.

OUT! LBW! Sibley cannot survive the day! The review does not do him any favors and such a heartbreaking end to the day for Dom Sibley. He batted wonderfully throughout the day but right towards the end, with just 3 balls remaining, he has departed. A Bumrah special finally gets the better of Dom Sibley. These things can happen in the final over of the day. The batter looks to block rather than score and the defensive mindset and tired legs sometimes do get the better of batters. Yorker on middle, Sibley is late in getting his bat down in time. He misses his flick and gets hit flush on the pad. A huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Sibley has a word with Root and without much confidence but rather hope, he decides to take the review. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows flatline as the ball goes past the bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows three reds. Sibley has to walk back and so do the other players.  But unlike Root, he will not walk out to bat tomorrow morning. STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Bumrah begins with a fuller length ball on off, from 'round the wicket, Stokes gets his bat down and jams it out to the off side.
On a good length this time, outside off and shaping away a shade, Stokes stays back to cover his stumps and shoulders arms.
Another delivery in the zone outside off, moving away again, Stokes leaves it to end the over.
Full and flighted on off, Root is on the back foot as he allows the ball to come to him and then blocks.
Root is away this morning! Fullish and outside off, Root pushes it in the gap at covers where Pujara makes a diving stop. A single is taken.
Loopy and on off, Stokes defends it close to his front pad.
Gives it a good toss and bowls it full around off, Stokes presses forward and pushes it to covers.
A slider on middle, skidding in, Stokes moves back and works it off his pads to mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball landing full around off, Stokes is behind the line and defends it back.
Good length delivery just outside off, Root moves across the stumps a bit and pushes it defensively to cover-point.
A bit too straight from Bumrah. He serves it full and around off, angling in, Root flicks it in front of square leg and gathers a single.
Back of a length delivery on off, Stokes chooses to stay on the back foot and plays it down to the left of point.
This time a length ball is angled into the left-hander, Ben rocks back and defends it solidly.

Wow! A terrific delivery! Stokes is very lucky to survive. Bumrah spears in a perfect yorker, right in the blockhole, Stokes brings his bat down and is lucky to get some part of his willow on it. The ball then deflects off his boot, beats the stumps and rolls behind to Pant. Bumrah has his hands on his head. That was a lucky escape for the Big Ben!
FOUR! Deft placement. Stokes opens his account. Width on offer outside off, Ben stays back and runs it down to third man fence for a boundary.
Flighted and full on off, Root is on the front foot in defense.
Advances down the track to a full ball and pushes it towards mid on.
Once again Root is nimble on his feet and eases a full ball in the direction of mid on.
Leans forward and across to a full ball and defends it on the leg side.
Spinning down the leg side, Joe flicks it towards square leg and picks up a run.
Flatter and a touch quicker around middle and leg, Stokes defends it from the inner half to square leg.
Hurls across a length delivery in the channel outside off, Root covers his stumps and then allows it through.
A length delivery on middle and off, skidding off the surface, Root is slightly squared up in defense and is hit high on the pads.
Too full in length and around off, Root does well to keep it out safely.
FOUR! Well played! Short in length and wide outside off, Root loves it there. He camps back and slaps it through backward point for a boundary.
Fullish and on off, angling in, Root defends it back.
Bumrah searches for a yorker but it ends up being a full toss on off, Root brings a straight bat down and pushes it to mid on.
Floated and full around off, Stokes leans forward and defends it to covers.
A touch flatter and shorter on off, Stokes goes back and plays it down to point.
Lands it full and wide outside off, Stokes tries to drive but it takes the inner half and rolls back to the bowler. Ashwin makes a half-stop in his followthrough
SIX! This one is dismissed! Stokes wears his skates to run down to the pitch of the ball and lofts it handsomely over long off for a biggie.
Full and flighted close to off, this time Ben strides forward and blocks it watchfully.
Beaten! Good response from Ashwin. He slows it up in the air and lands it full around off. The ball lands and breaks away to beat the forward defensive prod of Stokes. Good contest!
Angles in a good length ball on off, Root defends it back watchfully.
On and around off, a length ball, Root is firmly behind the line as he blocks it to the off side.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Bumrah keeps probing with a fuller length around off, Root does well to defend it right near his front pad.
Dishes out a fuller length ball on off, Root pushes it back defensively to the bowler. Bumrah doesn't collect it cleanly as he tries to mime a throw at the batsman.
Gets behind the line of the delivery to defend. But it possibly takes the bottom half of his blade and rolls behind. Root immediately turns to disallow the ball from going onto the stumps.
A flatter and shorter slider on middle, Stokes punches it down to mid on.
A touch short again, landing around off and turning away, Stokes stays back and keeps his bat away as the ball spins past.
Fullish and around off, Stokes pushes it off his front foot to covers.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Loopy and full around off, Stokes lunges and defends it back.
Once again Ashwin bowls a fuller length ball on off, Stokes happily defends it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery outside off, Root stays back and defends it down towards point.
Fuller in length and close to off, Root is behind the line as he defends it back to the bowler.
Serves a good length delivery outside off, Root stays rooted to the crease and allows it through to the keeper.

Shout for an lbw! Not given. Ishant spears in a very full ball on middle and leg, a hint of swing, Root fails to flick and is hit on the pads. A strong appeal follows but it appears to be sliding down the leg side. No review taken by India and rightly so.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Ishant probes with a length ball on off, Root stays back-footed and defends it solidly. Holds his pose and then checks where he ended up playing that shot.
Fuller and on off, Stokes sweeps it across the line but doesn't get it away from the middle of the bat. Ends up dragging it to the right of short fine leg for a run.
Fuller and on off, Root flicks it on the leg side, finds short mid-wicket.
Floated and full on off, Joe drives it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery, landing full on middle Root flicks it past the diving short mid-wicket fielder for a run.
Flatter and a touch shorter on off, Stokes goes on the back foot and defends.
That's a brave leave! Ashwin hurls across another slider, this time outside off, Stokes decides to offer no shot. It skids back in a shade and goes perilously close past the off pole.
Edgy! Good length ball on off, Root stays back to push it through the line but it takes the inner edge and rolls to square leg for a run. The slowness of the surface possibly coming into play.
Ishant, as expected, switches to 'round the wicket for the left-hander. He delivers a full ball on off, Stokes defends it to the off side.
Fullish and on off, Stokes drives it back to the bowler.
A length ball is angled into the batsman, around off, Stokes walks across and defends it towards mid off.

On a length and close to off, Stokes pushes it defensively down the ground and spots an opportunity to rotate the strike. He completes the run with ease as the mid on fielder stops the ball with his boot.
No run, Beaten! Lovely delivery, angling in around off and then nipping away a bit, Root feels for it inside the line and misses. We are done with 100 overs and England are 284/3!
Quicker delivery, short and on middle, Stokes goes back and defends it to the leg side.
A touch short and outside off, Stokes cuts it but finds the extra cover fielder. Wasn't middled well.
FOUR! Here comes the slog sweep! Full and floated landing on middle, spinning away very slightly, Stokes goes down on one knee and slogs it over square leg for a boundary.
Ashwin pulls his length back and bowls it quicker on middle, Ben works it off his pads in front of square leg for a run.
Loopy and full around off, Root presses forward and defends it back.
Fullish and down the leg side, it's swept on line down to long leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Root decides to defend it from the comfort of his crease.
Good length delivery just outside off, Root is on the back foot as he defends it to covers.

Big shout for an lbw! Once again the umpire shakes his head. Going down. Ishant arrows in a fuller length delivery on middle and leg, Root fails to flick and is pinged on the pads. The appeal is not entertained by the umpire. This has happened for the second time in the last two overs of Sharma. Root needs to be careful while trying to execute that shot.
Around off on a length, Root stays back and defends it to the off side.
Outside off, tapped down from the back foot to gully.
Pitches it up and around off, Root keeps it out safely towards covers.
Straightaway Stokes plays the reverse-batted shot. Full and around off, Ben reverse sweeps but finds point.
Flatter delivery, around middle and staying low, Stokes goes back and does well to defend it.
Fuller and on middle, Ben uses his wrists and flicks it in front of square leg for a run.
Tossed up ball around off, a bit on the shorter side, Root chooses to defend it from the back foot to the off side.

FOUR! Root goes down on one knee, fetches a full ball from outside off and sweeps it through square leg. Ishant rushes across to his left from fine leg, puts in a slide to stop the ball but then it clips his back leg and rolls to the fence. Good effort but in vain.
That is defended solidly off the front foot. An ordinary first over by Shahbaz.
FOUR! Shot! Fuller length ball on middle and leg, Stokes leans forward and across before whipping it off his pads through wide mid on. The fielder chases it but fails to pull it back.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Big Ben! 300 comes up for England. Ishant overcorrects his line and bowls it fuller around off, Stokes leans into the drive and thumps it through covers.
Fullish and on off, Stokes gets forward and pushes it down to mid on.
Miscued shot! Fuller length delivery outside off, Stokes tries to drive it through the line but it takes the inner half of his blade and rolls to mid on.
Too full and around off, Stokes brings down a straight bat in defense.
Once again Stokes is solidly behind the line of a length ball and defends it back.
Landed outside off, staying low, pushed towards cover.
Fuller, around off, driven through the covers for a single.
Improvising a little bit. That is what he is known for. Full and around middle, Stokes gets down and laps it over leg slip. Two runs taken.
Outside off, slow turn in, dabbed to first slip.
Short and around off, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
Short and outside off, punched through the covers for one.
Short and around off, punched back to the bowler.
Full and around off, well defended.
Slower through the air, shorter, defended to the off side.
Around off, punched down to mid-wicket for a run.
Short, around middle, worked straight to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, punched towards cover for one. Stokes moves to 30 from 49 balls.
Landed outside off, spinning in, defended out.
Full and outside off, Stokes reaches out and sweeps it, off the top edge, towards fine leg. No one there for the catch. A single taken.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler..
This is outside off, eased towards cover.
Landed outside off, spinning in, pushed towards mid off. Wants a single but then changes his mind.
Full and outside off, Root looks to drive but gets an edge. Well wide of cover. A run taken.
Landed outside off, spinning in, Root goes back and punches it towards point for a single. 50-RUN STAND COMES UP!
Quicker one on middle, well defended.
Landed aound leg, Stokes looks to play the reverse sweep but finds point.

India lose a review. Full and around off, Ben looked to play the reverse sweep. He missed and to the naked eye, it seemed like it lobbed off the glove, well wide of slip. Ashwin appealed for LBW, but there was no conviction. Strangely, Kohli went for the review. The first replay confirms it was glove. India lose a reviw but one feels it was tactical, just to slow things a bit.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Around off, defended from the crease.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.

Unfortunate for India. It never looked like going over. Full and around middle, Root lunged to defend but missed and was hit on the pads. Nadeem appealed but the umpire was firm. Kohli had a chat with Pant and one feels he says it might have gone over. Kohli goes for the review though. Ball Tracker shows the ball to be going over leg stump. Another review gone.
Full and outside off, swept to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Landed outside off, spinning in, worked towards short leg.
Ahh.... outside off, short in length, Stokes goes back, looks to cut but misses. The ball suddenly rears up, takes the gloove but falls safely down the leg side.
Spin from outside off again, Ben looks to work it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the thigh.
Outside off, pushed towards cover for a single.
Landed outside off, slightly squared up, pushed towards point.

DROPPED! Tough chance. Full and outside off, Stokes jumps out and looks to go over mid on. However, the ball lands on he rough and spins in. Hence, the leading edge is induced. It goes to the right of Ashwin who is moving to his left and hence, cannot quite react quickly enough. The ball bursts through his fingers and a single is taken.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Around off, easd towards cover.
Around off, spinning in, worked straight to square leg.
Full and outside ff, Stokes looks to sweep but misses and is hit on the pads. Huge LBW shout but impact outside off.

ANOTHER DROP! But a fabulous effort from Cheteshwar Pujara. Full and wide outside off, Stokes reaches out and plays a full-blooded sweep. The ball is flat and Pujara flings himself to his left at mid-wicket. He goes one-handed but the ball just bursts through. Two runs taken.
Around off, eked out towards point for a single.
150 FOR THE ENGLAND CAPTAIN! Another stunning innings. Gets there with a gentle push towards point.
Outside off, pushed back to the bowler.

SIX! CLOBBERED! Stokes is not going to hang around. Especially with the pitch starting to play tricks now. Full and outside off, Ben gets under this and slog sweeps this massively over mid-wicket. The stand moves to 63 and BS moves to 41.
Full and around off, worked wide of mid on, to his right, for a single.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Oohhh... looks to whip this one, but gets a leading edge towards mid off.
Full and outside off, watchfully blocked out this time.

RUN OUT CHANCE, MISSED! Around off, Stokes works this towards the left of square leg and sets off for a single. Root is gone for all money but the fielder throws it well wide of Pant, to his right and Joe gets in!
Around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, slow turn, Stokes looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! What a shot. High degree of risk, but Stokes plays that so well. Full and around off, Ben goes down, reaches out and reverse sweeps it over point!

FOUR! Consecutive boundaries and that's 50 FOR BEN STOKES. Very important for England. They cannot be an Australia and rely only one one man. The others need to chip in. Full and around leg, Ben reverse sweeps this along the carpet this time, through point.
Around off, BS goes back to defend.
Fuller, around off, defended from the crease again.
And another action replay.
Full and around off, Root lunges and flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, spinning in, punched through the covers for a single.
Landed outside off, slower through the air, Stokes goes back and defends.
Quicker through the air this time, watchfully blocked from the back foot.
Tossed up, outsideoff, a touch wide, Ben reaches out and clobbers an off drive but straight to Shahbaz Nadeem at mid off.
Shorter, around middle, blocked in front of short leg.
Shorter, around off, worked to the leg side.
Fuller, outside off, tossed up, watchfully defended.
Full again, outside off, swept hard but straight to square leg.

Ooh... that kicked up. Short, outside off, Root goes back to flick but the ball suddenly rears up, makes Joe lose control of his bat and hits him on the gloves. Root smiles because England are 337/3. But the pitch is starting to play tricks.
Comes down the track now and works it wide of mid on for a single.
Around middle, helped towards short mid-wicket.
A length ball, around off, helped wide of mid on for a single.
A length ball, around off, coming in, watchfully tucked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, towards short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven towards mid off.
Around middle, nudged towards square leg for a single.

Ripper of a delivery! But exceedingly well played as well. This is why Bumrah is so dangerous. He is not about inswingers or outswingers. He fires a yorker, just around off. But Root is watching the ball like a hawk and digs it out perfectly. Excellent cricket all around.
Around middle, pushed towards the bowler.
Fuller, around leg, pushed towards Sundar again.
Outside off, worked towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Not quite of the middle of the bat but Stokes gets a boundary. Full and outside off, Ben looks to put the pressure and gets down to play the slog sweep. Gets it off the toe end of the bat but bisects md-wicket and mid on. The stand moves to 81.
Around off, slower through the air, watchfully defended.

FOUR! Goes again and gets away with it again. Full and around off, Stokes plays another sweep, again he cannot get it off the middle of the bat, ends up dragging it, but it is in the gap between mid-wicket and mid on.
Landed outside off, dabbed towards gully.

Angled in from outside off, pushed towards cover for a single. The best seat in the house right now. That is what Joe Root is saying to Ben Stokes. I will get to the other end and watch the fun while you bat.
Full and outside off, very close to the sticks, left alone. Risky.

FOUR! Third boundary in the last five balls for Stokes. Full and around middle, Ben just works it through mid-wicket and gets a boundary. It is not a bad ball, as if he misses, he is gone LBW. But he connects. Moves to 63 and takes the partnership to 90.
Around off, watchfully defended.

Full and around off, BS drives it towards mid off. That will be the end of the over. Or not. Because the umpire has his right hand stretched out. He has been informed by his partner upstairs that Bumrah has overstepped. So we will have another ball.
Goes for the yorker, but dishes out a low full toss on middle, Stokes pushes it towards mid on.
Tossed up, outside off, driven straight to cover.
Fuller, around off, watchfully defended.
Leans, works this towards Rohit Sharma at deep mid on and sets off for a single. But Stokes sends him back immediately. That was hit powerfully. England don't want a mix up right now.
Gets the single this time. Goes back, converts the length into a short one and punches it through cover.
Fuller, around leg, pushed back to the bowler.
Slower delivery to finish. On the pads, watchfully blocked out. LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Starts off with a back of a length delivery on off, Root plays it to gully.
Leg bye! First run of this session corutesy an extra! On the pads, Root looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. Leg bye taken.
Well wide outside off, swings away further. Left alone.
Length and outside off, Stokes does not fiddle with it.
Stokes walks down the track to negotiate the swing. It does work for him as Ishant shortens his length. It is worked towards square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, Root stands tall and plays it onto the gronud. A tidy start by Ishant.
Starts off with one on the pads, Stokes works it to backward square leg.
This lands outside off, in the rough. Stokes looks to reverse sweep it by moving outside the line of off. He misses as there is extra bounce and is hit on the body.
A little too short this time, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Too short and put away! Someone who is batting on above 150 won't miss out. This is short and wide outside off, Root guides it through point and bags a boundary.
Better! On middle, nicely tossed up. Root blocks it.
A single to end! This is angled into the pads, Root works it through square leg for one. The century stand is up between the two.
Back of a length and on off, Root stays back and defends it onto the ground.
On the stumps, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Root pushes it to mid on. Too easy at the moment, there is swing for Ishant but it is coming off the wicket really slowly.
Lands it on a length around off, Root pushes it to covers.
Fuller and on off, Root hits it back towards the bowler. Ishant does well to get down and get a hand to it. He takes some pace off the ball and hence, only two as mid off does the mopping up job.
Back of a length and on off, Root stays back and defends it.
Dropped around off, spinning in, way too short, Stokes has ample time to rock back and pull it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, Root goes back and pushes it towards point.
Fuller, around off, pushed towards cover.
Dropped short, outside off, Joe goes back and pulls it to the right of Jasprit Bumrah at long on for a run.

SIX! CLOBBERED! That is the way he plays. We have seen Ben Stokes come under pressure while playing spinners outside his off stump but his way to counter that is by being attacking. So far, it has been working for him. Flighted, wide outside off, Ben comes down the track. Gets to the pitch of the ball and plays it with the spin over long on. The stand moves to 110 and BS has scored 72 of those.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Gets across and nudges this through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and just outside off, watchfully defended towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Not a bad idea, but not the greatest execution. Bumrah goes for the slower yorker, rolling his fingers over the ball. But it turns out to be a low full toss. It is on the stumps and Stokes is watchful. This is very important. Even though he is counter-attacking and has reached the 70s, he is not slogging wildly. Waits for the ball, spots it till the last moment and flicks it between mid on and mid-wicket.
Short and outside off, seaming away, Ben looks to pull but misses. Both batsman and bowler smile.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Landed outside off, Root goes back and pushes it behind point for a single.

Full and outside off, Stokes looks to play the reverse sweep but misses. Is hit on the pads and the ball lobs to square leg. 'JO KARNA HAI KARNE DO, HUM UDHAR HI DAALENGE, ' chides Pant. Meaning, 'Let them do what they want, we will bowl there only.' He is doing an excellent job to keep the Indian spirits high.

Landed outside off, Ben punches it through the covers and runs very well for the second. But great understanding from Rishabh Pant. He sees a tired Ishant Sharma at the cover boundary, so himself goes after the ball.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover for a single.
Brilliant batting. Root plays this against the spin, with soft hands, nurdles this through mid-wicket and even in this heat, runs back for the second. The stand moves to 121.
Full and around off, smothered out.
Landed outside off, Stokes angles this behind point. Shahbaz Nadeem goes after it, slides near the boundary and keeps the batsmen to a couple. Stokes moves to 81 now.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Angling away, on a length, pushed towards backward point.
Outside off, steered behind point for a single.
Full and down the leg side, Root misses his flick. Rishabh Pant dives full stretch to his left to stop that.
Landed outside off, a bouncer, Root sways away.

OUT! CAUGHT! Stop the press. India have taken a wicket at last. Is this the one to open the floodgates? And even this one was nearly dropped. Full and around off, Stokes continues his counter-attacking style and goes for the slog sweep. Connects well but perhaps, gets more height than he would have liked. The distance is not there. Cheteshwar Pujara is stationed at deep backward square leg and it is a regulation catch. He takes it, but oops, fumbles. Luckily for him, the ball goes through his palms, hits his knee and that helps him take it on the rebound. Smiles sheepishly. No real celebration from the Indians, they understand the value of this innings. 82 from 118 balls. Wow. Take a bow,  Ben Stokes. Could well be the difference between the two sides. The 124-run stand has been broken.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Turns this towards backward square leg for a single.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.

FOUR! Pope opens his account with a streaky boundary. Short and outside off, Ollie rocks back to cut but the extra bounce induces an outside edge. It flies in the air, but is well wide of Cheteshwar Pujara at backward point, to his left.
Full and around off, Ollie looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat back to the bowler.
A short ball, outside off, left alone.
Around off, Root gets across and nudges this through square leg for a single. The skipper moves to 170.
Landed outside leg, Pope misses his flick.
Length and around off, Pope guides it to point.
