That is a jaffa. On a good length, outside off, Ollie looks to defend. But the ball straightens and squares him up. Beats him and goes off something to the keeper. There is an unconvincing appeal for the catch but the umpire shakes his head. That went off the pad.
Full and around off, OP drives it towards mid off.
The arm ball, around off, Root goes back and punches it to the off side.
Slower through the air this time. Fuller, round off, Joe lunges to defend.
Down the leg side, easy picking for the skipper as he goes back and nudges this through mid-wicket for a single.
Slower through the air, outside off, Pope exhibits a good forward defense.
There comes the arm ball again, on middle, once more Ollie is solid in defending.
Ugly. Full and outside off, Pope reaches out, looks to sweep but misses. Nearly loses his balance.
Full and around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, around middle, worked towards square leg.
Goes for the yorker now, taking a cue from Bumrah, but Pope is upto it. Takes it on the full and flicks it towards mid-wicket. There is a hint of reverse visible.
Outside off, on a length, Ollie shoulders arms.
Full and straight, OP wrists it away but cannot beat short mid-wicket.
Fuller again, on middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket once more.
Landed outside off, spinning away, punched through the covers for a single.
Short and outside off, slow away turn, Pope misses out. Cuts it straight to point.
Fuller, a dart, around middle, blocked off the front foot. Another no ball, called by the third umpire.
Full again, but this is slower. Ollie looks to drive it through the covers but the ball pitches, turns in, takes the inside edge and goes to fine leg. A single taken.
Full and straight, comfortably swept to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Jumps out of the crease, is not quite to the pitch of the ball but manages to defend.
Better. Comes forward and defends watchfully.
A short ball, but wayward. Down the leg side. Root gets across and moves out of the way.

A short ball, outside off, Root goes back and comfortably pulls it all along the ground to deep mid-wicket for a single. 400 UP FOR ENGLAND. Something that Chris Silverwood wanted, England's head coach, when he took over - that England make 400 more often. It need not necessarily be a match-winning score but more often than not, it puts you in a dominant position.
Around middle, worked towards square leg.
Fuller, outside off, swinging away, driven towards mid off.

Fuller, around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket. Short mid-wicket gets across, looks to stop but fumbles and lets it through. Pope looks for the single but there is mid-wicket mopping up. But that lackadaisical effort has not gone unnoticed. 'C'MON BHAI!' yells Pant. The response is an apology from the fielder.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, Root goes back and defends.
Comes down the track and nurdles it towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller, around off, solidly defended off the front foot.
A dart, around middle, Root is quick to go back and defend.
Shorter, pushed towards mid on.
Steps out but this time slightly late, he works it through mid-wicket and keeps strike for the next over.
Around off, Root stays leg side of the ball and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Full and around off, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Around off, flicked towards short mid-wicket again.
Hat-trick of balls, played out to the leg side.
Full and around off, the reverse sweep comes out, towards point, for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Full and around middle, darted in, worked to the leg side.
Around middle, pushed back.
Tosses it up now. Pope blocks it.
Continues to bowl the middle and leg line, Pope finds the fielder at square leg
Down the leg side, helped past short mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, pushed towards point.
Tossed up, outside off, Pope lunges to defend.
A dart, around middle, Ollie keeps it out watchfully.
On middle, OP goes back and tucks it to the leg side.
Full and around off, Pope comes forward and defends.
Shortish, around middle, worked towards short leg.
Around middle, pushed to the leg side. First maiden for Washington Sundar in this innings. Good time to gain his confidence back, with a new batsman at the crease, looking tentative.
Full and around off, Root plays that as late as possible, getting his bat down at the last moment to defend.

FOUR! CLUBBED! A partner killer. Full and outside off, Root jumps down the track and hammers it straight back. Nearly takes Pope out of the way, who has to get down in a hurry. The ball races to the long on fence. Root moves to 181.
Full and outside off, slower through the air, the skipper looks to defend but the ball spins in, bounces, takes the inside edge, hits the body and drops down.
Around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, pushed towards the bowler.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Mix up, but safe! Full and around midddle, Root goes back and works it to the leg side. Pope is late to respond but the single is eventually completed with ease.
Another single as this is worked through mid-wicket.

FOUR! 'You could have done better, Ash', chides Pant. Full and around middle, Pope comes down the track and hits it straight back. Ashwin makes a laboured effort to his left at mid on but cannot stop it. The ball races to the long on fence.
Continues to bowl it around off, Pope blocks it.
A little flatter and on off, Ollie stays back and defends it.
On the stumps once again, Pope has enough time to play this off the back foot and onto the ground.
Ollie uses his feet now, does not get to the pitch of it but adjusts and works it well with the turn to mid-wicket.
Around off, Root goes back and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Around off, watchfully defended.

Confusion but safe! In the last few minutes, Pope and Root have been making some confusing calls. This time, Pope works it through mid-wicket and calls for a single. He is halfway down the track but Root calmly sends him back. Pope gets in with a dive but both batsmen were ball-watching.
On middle and leg, defended back.
Works this straight to squre leg.

Pope survives a review from India! And with that, the hosts have exhausted all their reviews for this innings. Full and around leg, Ollie looked to sweep. The ball lobbed off something to Ajinkya Rahane at somewhere around leg gully. India appeal for the catch but nothing from umpire or even Ajinkya Rahane. Yet, Kohli goes for the review. Ball Tracker shows no spike when the ball passes the bat or glove. They check for the LBW but Ball Tracker is showing the ball to bounce over. Desperation from India.

FOUR! Cheeky from Root. Quick delivery, outside off, Joe takes it on the full and reverse sweeps it to third man. Gets past Inzamam-ul-Haq in the list of leading run getters in Test cricket. The stand moves to 33.
Full and around off, driven through the covers for a single.
Comes down and flicks it owards long on for a run.
Action replay of the previous delivery.
Outside off, pushed through cover for a single.
Works it towards mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, worked towards square leg.
Rotation of strike. Goes back and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Around middle, stubbornly defended.
Landed outside leg, Root reverse sweeps it towards backward point. Quick single taken.
Outsie off, Pope leans and pushes it towards cover for a run. The stand moves to 40.
Short and around middle, the skipper pulls it through mid-wicket where Ajinky Rahane does well to get across to his right to keep the batsmen to a single.
Short, outside off, Root goes back and punches it towards backward point for another quick single.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep point for a run.
Around middle, worked through square leg for one.
Full and around off, well defended.
Short and outside off, cut straight to backward point.

Massive, massive shout for LBW. Not given and India do not have any review left. Full and around off, Pope lunged to defend but the ball went on with the arm and hit him on the pads. To the naked eye, it seemed like an inside edge. Yes, replay confirms.
Outside off, reverse paddled to short third man for a single.
The conventional sweep now, towards square leg in the deep for a run.

SIX! What a way to get to your 200! Three of his last 4 hundreds have been doubled. Is Graham Gooch happy with daddy hundreds? Someone is finally listening to him. Full and around middle, Root comes down the track and sends it sailing over long on. The helmet is off and a big smile flashes across. What a knock. Superb.
Comes down the track and works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Around middle, Pope comes down the track and defends.
Short and outside off, cut towards point for a single.
Short and outside off, cut towards point.
Outside off, cut straight to point.
Lucky! Full and outside off, Pope gets down to play the paddle but misses. The ball takes the inside edge, misses the off stump and beats Pant! A couple taken.
Well, he goes for the paddle again. Connects properly this time, for a single to fine leg.
Sliding on with the arm, pushed towards square leg.
Low full toss, outside off, pushed towards long on for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Floated wide outside off, Pope reaches out and drives it towards long off for a run. The stand moves to 60.
Fuller, around middle, wristed towards short mid-wicket.
Shorter, outside leg, Root goes back and works it through square leg for one.
Nicely bowled. Bit of loop outside off, OP goes back and punches it through the covers for another single.
Landed outside off, spinning away, left alone.
450 UP FOR ENGLAND. Short and outside off, Pope rocks back and cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
The arm ball, around middle, Root goes back and defends.
Fired through, on middle, pushed back again.
Outside off, a bit of a loop, outside off, let through.
Full and outside off, Root lunges, has to fetch it, looks to play the sweep, miscues it, gets a top edge but it does not carry to deep mid-wicket. A run taken.
Tossed up, outside off, driven through the covers for a single.
Around off, spinning in, Pope stays back and works it towards short mid-wicket.
More flight, outside off, Ollie jumps out, but is not quite to the pitch of the ball. Defends.
Around off, nudged to the leg side.
Short and outside off, slapped towards sweeper cover for a single.
Looped up, outside off, pushed down to long on for a run. TEA ON DAY 2!
Starts off with what seemed like a slower one on middle, Root defends it.
Back of a length and on off, Root defends it. The siren goes on which means it is another no ball!
Good timing! Shorter and around off, Root pushes it through covers. It is away from the fielder in the deep. Two taken.
Length and outside off, Root leaves it alone. No carry at for Bumrah.
One more length delivery on off, Root is solid in defense.
Outside off, Root plays it late but to point.
Root keeps strike now as he pushes this ball on off through point for one.
Flatter and on middle, Root works it on the leg side.
Quicker and on middle, this is defended.
On middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
A single now as this is pushed down to long on.
Slower through the air and on off, Pope blocks it out.
On the pads to end, Pope works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
EDGY FOUR! England won't mind how they come as long as they do! This is on a length and outside off, Pope looks to drive it on the up but it goes through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Really well fielded by Ashwin! On middle, Pope pushes it firmly towards mid on. Ashwin there runs to his left, dives and stops it.
Very full and on middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, Root pushes it back to the bowler.
On the off pole, Root stands back and keeps it out onto the ground.
On middle, Pope works it towards mid-wicket.
Very nicely played! This is slow and tossed up outside off, Pope plays the reverse sweep, just uses the pace of the bowler and hits it through short third man for two.
Top edge but safe! This is floated up on off, Pope looks to sweep but gets a top edge. It goes over the keeper who has no idea where the ball is and towards third man for two.
On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on the stumps, Pope works it to mid-wicket.
Another one on the pads, Pope nudges it on the leg side.
Flatter and on middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
A little too full, this is eased down to long off for one.
Slightly shorter, this one stays a touch low. Pope cuts it through point for one.
One more single! On middle, Root works it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Quicker and on middle, Pope pushes it to covers.
Fuller this time, gives it more air. Pope strokes it to covers.
On middle, Root goes back and works it through mid-wicket for one.

OUT! LBW! That is as plumb as it gets! Pope's scratchy innings comes to an end! He just never got going and seemed like struggling throughout. Ashwin gets his second. The carom ball does the trick for him. It lands on middle and then straightens a touch. Pope ends up playing down the wrong line and is hit on the pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Pope does not review and rightly so.

Just short! This is brilliantly bowled! Ashwin gives it a lot of flight, slows it up outside off. Buttler is early into the drive. He is early because of the slowness of the surface. It goes off the inner half. It goes uppishly but lands just short of Gill who dived forward. He fails to stop it and a single is taken.
On off, blocked.
Another one tossed up nicely and it lands on off, Root keeps it out.
Another dot to end! On middle, Root blocks it onto the ground.
Flatter and on middle, this is pushed to the right of the bowler.
Close! Goes back to a delivery which he should be forward to. Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.
On the shortish side outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Angled into the pads, this is nudged around the corner for one.
Fires it on off, Root guides it to point.

OUT! Three reds and Root's fine, fine innings comes to an end! Handshakes from a few Indian players as he walks back towards the pavillion! End of a marathon innings! Nadeem though gets his second. This is lands on middle and then straightens just a touch. Root looks to work it on the leg side but misses. It hits the front pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Root reviews immediately and signals that he feels it is going down with the angle. Ball Tracker shows it to be straightening and hitting the stumps. He takes a review along with him. This is a good passage of play for India.
Floats it up on off, Buttler defends it onto the ground.
On off, this is defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Tosses it up on middle, Bess flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle again, Bess nudges it to short leg.
Slower through the air on middle, Bess lets it come to him and then works it to mid-wicket.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Solid! On the stumps, Buttler lunges and keeps it out nicely.
On the off pole, Jos pushes it through covers for one.
Slows it up, lands it outside off, Bess lets it be.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Close! on off, this one comes in with the angle. Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge past the leg pole and down to the fine leg fielder for one.
Full and around middle, driven back to the bowler.
Around middle, helped in front of short leg.
Around middle, watchfully defended.
Full and around middle, Jos lunges to defend. The ball spins in, goes off the pad, past the keeper, to his left but Cheteshwar Pujara dives to his right at leg slip to stop the ball.
Around off, defended watchfully.
Punched down to long on for a single.
Outside off, pushed to the off side.
Full and around off, swept around the corner, towards fine leg for a couple.
Goes back and dabs it to the off side.
The arm ball, outside off, Buttler is solid in defense.
Full and around off, another sweep, this time for a single to deep backward square leg.
Tries to use his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball and pushes it towards mid on.
Outside off, spinning in, watchfully defended.
Full and around off, Buttler lunges to push it back to the bowler.
Around off, worked to the leg side. 129 balls left in the day, 103 minutes remaining (extended).
Spins in a long way from outside off, nudged towards short fine leg.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards square leg.
Down the leg side again, kept out towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
The arm ball, around middle, Bess stays back to block.
Good leave. Or lucky. Tossed up, outside off, Dom lets it go, expecting the ball to turn but the ball goes straight on. Just misses off stump.
Hmmm... this is well tossed up and that generates extra bounce. DB lunges to defend but there is an inside edge taken. Goes wide of short leg.
Fuller, around off, well defended.
Full and around off, driven back to the bowler.
FOUR! Fine shot. Outside off, Buttler goes back and punches it through the covers for a boundary. Moves to 13 and Buttler moves to 12.
FOUR MORE! Cry of 'NO!' from Ashwin as soon he let the ball go. Short, wide outside off, Buttler rocks back and just puts bat to ball. It rockets through cover.
Fuller, around off, watchfully defended.
More flight, around off, Jos goes back to defend.
Fired in on leg stump, JB lunges to keep it out.
Down the leg side, helped in front of short leg.
Down the leg side, Bess looks to flick but misses. It goes off something to short fine leg. A leg bye signalled.
Slowly looped up, coming from a wider angle, from around the wicket, fuller, around middle, Buttler defends.
Around off, Jos dead-bats it to the off side.
Fuller, around off, pushed through the covers for a single.
Full, around middle, kept out watchfully.
Quicker one, around middle, Bess has to keep that out in a hurry.
Around off, Buttler stays back to defend.
Fuller, around off, Jos reaches out to push it away.
Outside off, pushed away from his body towards cover.
Full and flat, outside off, JB is back to defend.
Comes from around the wicket, lands it around leg, Buttler looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his pads and lobs towards point.
Adventurous. Tossed up, outside off, Jos looks to drive but is not quite to the pitch of the ball. Gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Around middle, defended solidly.
Comes down the track, shows a bit of aggresion but is not to the pitch of the ball. Goes big, but mistimes it towards mid on.
Fuller, but less flighted, well defended. 99 balls left in the day, 90 minutes remaining (extended).
Landed outside off, spinning away a touch, left alone.
Slower one, more flight, outside off, let through again.
Full and around leg, worked through square leg for a single.
A full toss, on middle, Bess is surprised, initially looking to flick, before adjusting in the end to defend.
This one lands, around middle, defended watchfully.
Comes down the track and pushes it towards long on for a single. The stand moves to 20.

Massive, massive shouts for caught behind! Umpire Anil Chaudhury is unmoved. Sundar is on his haunches. There was no close-in fielder who did not appeal or did not feel that it was out. Full and outside off, Buttler looked to push but missed. Rishabh Pant immediately went up and Sundar too, joined in convincingly. Short leg, silly point, first slip, leg slip, all chipped in. Sundar started to actually plead with the umpire, but nothing doing. India do not have a review left. Waiting to see what technology shows.
FOUR! SUBLIME! Rubbing salt on the wounds. Full and outside off, Buttler leans and drives this gloriously through the covers. 500 UP FOR ENGLAND.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Tossed up, outside off, Bess jumps out, gets to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over mid off.
Around middle, worked to the leg side.
This is pushed back to the bowler.
Landed outside off, Bess watches it go past. Very close to the off pole.
That beat everyone. Full and outside off, Bss lunges to defend. He misses, the ball bounces, goes over the stumps and beats Pant too. Goes off his arm to fine leg. A bye taken.
Full and around off, Bess uses his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it back to the bowler.
The arm ball, outside off, Dom lunges to defend but misses and is hit on the back thigh.
Comes down the track, looks to defend but gets an inside edge wide of Rohit Sharma at short leg. Short fine leg mops it up.
Comes out again, looks to defend but this time gets an outside edge towards third man. A run taken.

EDGED, FOUR! In between keeper and leg slip! Not really an opportunity. Full and around leg, Buttler looks to flick but the ball flies off the inside edge and even before Virat Kohli can react at leg slip, the ball is through, to the fine leg fence. 79 balls left in the day, 77 minutes remaining (extended).
Outside off, pushed towards point.
Comes down the track and flicks it towards square leg.
FOUR! Outside off, spinning in, Bess just nudges it through the vacant leg slip region. Moves to 12.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Bess goes back and punches it through point. The stand is worth 42 now.
Jumps out and drills it straight. But hits the stumps at the other end. Nadeem tries to get his foot in the way but misses. Buttler was out of his crease. The ball deflects towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, pushed towards point. Another no ball calld by the third umpire. 16th for India, 6th for Nadeem in this innings.
Around middle, worked through fine leg for a single.
Outside off, pushed through point for a run.
Outside off, Bess comes down the track and pushes it towards point.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Comes down the track and defends. 69 balls left in the day, 71 minutes remaining (extended).
Short and outside off, pushed towards point.
Full and around middle, worked to the leg side.
Around off, going straight on, squares Bess up who pushes it towards point.

EDGED, FOUR! Streaky. Short and outside off, Buttler looks to cut but without moving his feet. Gets an inside edge which shoots past the off stump, to the left of Rishabh Pant and into the fine leg fence.

OUT! Arms are shouldered and the off stump is rattled! Misjudgement from Buttler and this is not the first time in his career. Anyone who followed the Ashes would remember the way the Aussies dismissed him in 2019. Keep it outside off, just a fraction wide and then make it come back in. Buttler feels this will not come back in enough or if it does, will go over. But to his horror, it comes back in at stump height and pegs the off stump back. End of a 48-run stand.

OUT! BOWLED! Wicket number 299 for Ishant in Tests. After toiling hard for 23 wicketless overs, he has got 2 in 2 balls. Fuller length this time, around off, Archer looks to defend. But by the time the bat can come down, the ball is through. Hits the top of off stump.

Aahhh. nearly gets through Leach. Cramps him up, gets this to angle in from around the wicket, Jack pushes at it and the ball goes off the outside edge behind point. The batsmen take a single. The siren goes out, indicating that Ishant has overstepped. No ball number 17 of the innings.
Down the leg side, Bess looks to tuck but misses and is hit on the pads. The ball deflects to the leg side and a leg bye is taken.
Around off, defended to the off side.
EDGED, DOES NOT CARRY! Full and outside off, Leach looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball lands just short of Virat Kohli at wide first slip. Excellent over from Ishant.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
This one goes on with the arm, Bess looks to defend but is squared up. Is beaten on the outside edge.
Comes down the track and blocks.
Pushes this down to long on for a single.
Full and around middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Comes down the track and flicks it towards short mid-wicket.

Caught behind? The slips seemed interested. Ishant was the last one to join in. That was a giveaway. Outside off, Leach looks to cut but misses. The slips went in first, putting in a huge appeal and then Pant joined in. Feeling left out, Ishant joined the party but the umpire was unmoved. As per the replay, seems like a big gap between bat and ball.
Outsie off, on a length, Jack looks to play but misses.
Landed outside off, once again JL wants to feel bat on ball but misses again.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Landed outside off, Leach feels for it but misses. 49 balls left in the day, 49 minutes remaining (extended).
Outside off, pushed towards gully where Ajinkya Rahane stops it.
Full and outside off, Bess lunges to defend but misses.
Comes down the track and nudges it towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, Dom stays back to defend.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Comes down the track and pushes it towards long on for a single.
Full and around middle, pushed to the leg side.
On a length, around off, pushed to the leg side.
A bouncer, outside off, Bess thinks about the pull but then bails out.
On a length, outside off, jags back in, Dom looks to defend but misses and is hit on the pads. Mild shouts for LBW. Too high an impact. 39 balls left in the day, 43 minutes remaining (extended).
FOUR LEG BYES! Full and down the leg side, Bess misses his flick but the ball hits his pads and deflects past Rishabh Pant, to his left, to the fine leg fence. The stand moves to 10.
Ooohh... almost a Jos Buttler's dismissal replica! Full and outside off, reversing in, Bess shoulders arms, the ball comes back in and narrowly misses off stump!

Another appeal for LBW, more convincing from Ishant this time, but nothing from the keeper or anyone else. Full and around middle, Dom missed his flick and was hit on the pads. Ball Tracker shows it to be clipping leg stump.

DROPPED! Shocker from Rohit Sharma. Full and around middle, Bess comes down the track and looks to flick. But his bat hits the ground and the ball lobs off the face of the bat. It goes straight to Rohit Sharma at short mid-wicket, who looks to take the catch near his face but somehow, inexplicably, puts it down!
Outside off, guided past first slip towards third man for a single. Bess moves to 20.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Full and straight, kept out again.
Around middle, helped to the leg side.

Outside off, smothered in front of silly point. Have to feel for Washington Sundar. Has bowled his heart out today. But luck has not been with him. Could have had Buttler but the umpire did not agree while in this over, Rohit dropped a sitter.
Around off, coming in, pushed towards point. 29 balls left in the day, 35 minutes remaining (extended).
Length ball outside off, pushed towards cover.
Around middle, well defended.
Very full, almost a yorker, dug out well.
FOUR! Down the leg side, Bess tickles it towards fine leg. There is a fielder but the ball beats him to his right.
Full and down the leg side, Bess misses his flick.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
FOUR! That has come out of nowhere. Flighted outside off, Leach steps out, takes the bowler on and clears mid off! The stand moves to 20.
Around middle, dabbed to the leg side.
Full and around middle, Jack lunges to push it away.
Shorter in length, JL goes back and works it towards short mid-wicket. 19 balls left in the day, 29 minutes remaining.
Goes back and blocks it out.
FOUR! Outside off, on a length, Bess pushes this away from his body, behind point and gets a boundary.
On a length, outside off, pushed towards point.
Full and around off, more reverse, watchfully driven towards cover.
Very full, on the stumps, nearly goes through, but Bess gets his bat down at the last moment to defend.
Outside off, pushed towards point.
Goes for the yorker, but it turns out to be a low full toss. Flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Around middle and leg, helped to the leg side.
Full and outside off, driven towards cover.
Goes right back in his crease to defend. 9 balls left in the day, 22 minutes remaining.

Ooohh... the carrom ball, outside off, Leach looks to drive but the ball darts back in, stays low, beats the inside edge and misses the off stump. Excellently taken by Rishabh Pant. The siren goes off again, to signal no ball number 18 for the innings.
Very full, around middle, pushed towards mid off.
Outside off, the carrom ball, rips back in, Jack looks to defend but gets aninside edge onto his pads. Ashwin solely appeals for LBW but in vain.
Stay back and keeps it out.
Around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, dabbed towards point. Another no ball called by the third umpire.
FOUR LEG BYES! Down the leg side, Bess looks to tickle but the ball goes off his pads, past Rishabh Pant, to his left and into the fine leg fence.The stand moves to 30.
Down the leg side again, again Bess misses his flick and is hit on the pads. The ball goes to square leg this time.
Full and around off, defended back to the bowler. Bumrah collects and back-flicks it onto the stumps at the non-striker's end. Hits them but Leach never moved.
Outside off, played straight to cover.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on. STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Fuller ball around off to begin, Leach pushes it towards cover.
Full again, this one is driven towards mid off and takes a quick single.
Floated around off, Bess defends it off the front foot.
Flat and around middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Bess this time dances down the track and drives it towards mid off.
Floats the last ball just around off, it is poked towards the man at point.
Fuller ball to begin from Bumrah. Leach comes on the front foot and looks to defend. The ball takes the toe end and goes to the slip cordon.
Goes for the magic delivery. Brilliant yorker from Bumrah. Leach looks to keep it out but ends up getting an inside edge on the pad. Hang on! It is a no ball.
Nails the yorker this time. It is just outside off and Leach cannot keep it out.
Angles a length ball from around off, Leach looks to work it on the leg side but it takes the inside edge and goes towards the leg side.
Good length and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Fuller and around off, Bess drives it towards mid on.
Full and on off, Bess comes on the front foot towards the off side.
Floated on off, Leach drives it towards cover-point and get a single. The ball though takes the leading edge.
Floated around off, kept out.
Tossed up and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Flat and around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for one.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around off, poked towards point.
Length and outside off, Bess looks to defend it off the back foot but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball shapes away from him.
Another length ball outside, it holds its line as Bess looks to poke but is beaten.
Full and angled on the pads, Bess goes for the flick but gets beaten as the ball goes off the pads to square leg. A leg bye taken.
A brilliant yorker on off, Leach does well to dig it out.
Fuller and around middle, Leach clips it to mid-wicket.
WIDE! Short and on middle, Leach ducks under it. It is a bit high as the umpire gives it a wide.
Leach looks to flick it off his pads but is beaten as the ball goes to the left of Rishabh Pant.
FOUR! Fine shot! Tossed up from Ashwin, Bess dances down the track and powers it over mid-wicket and wide of the man at long on. Excellent stroke from him.
Floats this one around off, Bess comes on the front foot and blocks.
Floated around off, Bess comes down the track and pushes it towards mid off.
Bess dances down again, Ashwin slows it down. Bess defends it out.
Flat ad around off, it is tucked towards square leg for one.
Floatd around off, it turns in. Leach keeps it out off the back foot.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Good length and just outside off, Bess pokes at it but misses.

OUT! LBW!! The new ball works for India. Bumrah does the magic with it. The 9th wicket is gone down! India would feel that they should have had taken the new ball earlier. Nicely bowled length ball around middle, Bess looks to defend it to the leg side but ends up missing it. The ball raps him on the pads and there goes an appeal from Jasprit. The umpire's finger goes up and Dom Bess looks to review initially but then decides against it as he walks off.
Good length and around off, poked towards point for nothing.
Yorker outside off, Anderson keeps it out.
Shortish and around off, Anderson blocks. End of a successful over from Bumrah.
Darted on middle and leg, tucked on the leg side.
Edgy! Floated around middle and leg, Leach looks to defend but the ball spins in. It takes the inside edge, goes on the pad and then lobs towards the off side.
FOUR! Shot! Handy runs! Tossed up and outside off, Leach dances down the track and powers it over the bowler's head for a boundary.

Stumping chance missed! Oh, dear, Pant! A bit of extra bounce and Pant fails to collect the ball behind the wicket. Leach once again dances down the track and Ashwin smartly shortens the length. It spins away a touch as well. Leach is beaten all ends up. The ball bounces extra and Pant fails to collect. Another chance missed by Pant behind the wickets. The debate about him and Saha will stop again.
Tossed up and around off, pushed towards mid off for a single.

FOUR BYES! More runs against Pant. End of an eventful over. Floated around middle and leg, Anderson looks to slog sweep but the ball spins in and he is beaten. The keeper is beaten as well and it races away down to the fine leg fence. Missed the leg pole by just.
Leach blocks it off the back foot towards the bowler.
Full on off, Leach pushes it to mid off.
Short and outside off, Leach lets it be.
Short of good length around off, Leach hops and fends it away.
Full and around off, Leach drives but Pujara at covers does well to field it.
Short of length outside off, Leach looks to cut it uppishly but is beaten on the outside edge.
On off, pushed to the off side .
Floated on off, Anderson defends it out.
Full and outside off, Anderson goes for the reverse sweep but get it to the man at short third man.
Loopy and around off, driven towards the cover region.
On off, driven to long off for one.
Lands on middle and spins in past the flick. Pant collects it down the leg side. A muted appeal from him but turned down.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards point off the back foot.
Banged short down the leg side. Anderson looks to work it on the leg side but misses. Pant fails to collect the ball to his right. A bye taken.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Goes for the yorker but ends up dishing a full toss. Flicked to mid on for nothing.
Good length Good length and around off, pushed on the off side.
A bouncer and Leach sways away from the line.

OUT! Cleaned up! That ends England's marathon first innings. Ashwin gets the final wicket as England innings Tossed up around off, Anderson goes for the slog sweep but he gets beaten on the flight there. The ball though does not miss its target as it crashes into the middle pole. England BOWLED OUT FOR 578 RUNS!
False start from Anderson! He slips the first one down the leg side. Rohit looks to flick but misses to connect.
Rohit is up and running! A short ball, outside off, he punches it wide of the cover fielder for a single.
Gill is off the mark too! A fullish ball on the pads. Gill flicks it to deep backward square leg for a run.
Another one down the leg side. Rohit misses his flick again.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Good length and around off, Rohit is compact in defense. Decent start.
Nicely punched! A fullish ball just outside off to begin from Archer. Gill punches the drive through the covers for a brace.
Two more! This one is on the pads and on a fuller length again. Gill clips it through mid-wicket for two.
Around off on a length, pushed towards mid off.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Lovely from Archer! A length ball, just outside off, it pitches around off and a hint of away movement. Gill pokes at it away from his body to get beaten. This doesn't carry to the keeper.
FOUR! Take that! First boundary of the innings for the Indians. This is banged short and Gill takes him on. Pulls it through mid-wicket and finds the fence. Lovely finish to the over.
Fuller and around off, Rohit looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and it goes to square leg. A single taken.
A length ball around off, Gill defends it out.

FOUR! SHOT! This is brilliant stuff from Gill already! Just a push and it races away to the fence. A good length ball around off, Gill brings his bat down and punches it with straight bat. Super shot.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, kept out solidly.
Shortish and angled in. Gill looks to defend but the ball comes in a touch and hits his body.
Beaten! Archer is steaming in here! Lovely ball from him. Slightly shorter in length and just outside off, it moves away. Rohit looks to defend is beaten.

FOUR! Don't bowl him there, Archer! The Indians are too good off their pads and Rohit shows the proof. A fuller ball on middle and leg, Rohit uses his wrists and flicks it through square leg for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Archer strikes early. Superb comeback delivery from Archer and he sends Rohit packing. Early success for England. Another shortish length ball, just outside off, moves away a touch. Rohit pokes at it with hard hands. Ends up getting a nick behind and Buttler moves to his right to gobble up the chance. The dangerous Rohit has been removed. He could've easily left that alone this early in the innings. Poor from Rohit.
Pujara is up and running first ball. Another shortish length from Archer. Pujara taps it on the off side and gets to the other end.
In the channel outside off, Gill lets it be.
Good length and around off, kept out. End of a successful over from Archer.
Fuller and around off, Pujara is solid in defense.
Good length and around off, kept out by Pujara.
In the channel outside off, Pujara lets it go behind.
Short and wide outside off, Pujara forces it wide of point. Two taken before the fielder can get to the ball.
Fuller and just outside off, Pujara defends it towards gully with soft hands.
Full and around off, it comes in a touch. Pujara looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes wide of the man at silly mid on.
Good running! Shortish and around middle, Gill pushes it towards mid on and calls for a run. Makes it easily.
FOUR! Whipped! Top stuff from Pujara. A fuller ball on middle, Pujara flicks it through mid-wicket and finds his first boundary of the innings.
Good length and just around off, tapped on the off side and a loud no from Pujara.

Lovely from Archer! That is a peach from him. A length ball, around off, Pujara has to play at it. He does so but is beaten. A muted appeal from Buttler and Pujara. There was a noise but it was the bat brushing the pad. Top stuff from Archer here.
Full and around middle, flicked to mid on.
Full and just outside off, solidly punched towards the cover fielder this time.
Fuller and around off, punched towards silly mid on.
Good length and around off, kept out.
FOUR! On the pads again and Gill nails the flick. Fuller and on the pads, Gill flicks it hard through square leg. It goes wide of the man at deep square leg and it races to the fence.
Full and around off, played to silly mid on again. A solid defense from Gill.

FOUR! Nails the flick again. Gill moves to 22 now. Stunning batting from him. A fuller ball, on the pads again. Gill is strong there, he is very strong. Gets the bat down and flicks it through mid-wicket to find the 2nd boundary of the over.
Yorker and around off, kept out. 8 off the over.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Slips this one down the leg side. Pujara lets it be.
Confusion but safe. A length ball around middle, it is tucked towards mid-wicket. Pujara calls for the single first. Gill goes for the run but Pujara says no. Gill returns back in time.
Length ball around middle, tucked towards square leg for one.
A sharp bouncer from Archer. It is around off, Gill drops his wrists and lets it go to the keeper.

Ouch! Extra bounce for Archer there. A length ball around middle and leg, Gill looks to work it on the leg side. The extra bounce means the ball hits his glove and goes towards square leg. A single taken.
Short ball from Stokes to begin. Gill pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Shortish and just outside off, Pujara drops his wrists and lets it go.
Short ball around middle, kept out.
Good length and outside off, Pujara drops it in front of the cover region for a single.
Banged short and on middle, Gill sits under it.
Short again from Stokes and Gill pulls it through square leg for one.
FOUR! Punished again! Full again from Archer and Gill flicks it nonchalantly through mid-wicket for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Anderson with a stunning catch at mid on. Archer gets his man. Both the openers dismissed for India now. A fuller ball from Anderson. Gill punches the drive uppishly. He does that half-heartedly. The ball goes uppishly towards mid on. Anderson there quickly moves to his left and lunges forward to take the low catch. A fine catch from the veteran. His 97th catch in Tests. A solid knock from Gill but he will be disappointed. A fine track for batting but he falls.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Bangs short this time and Kohli ducks under it.

Sharp stuff from Archer. He's steaming in. He once again bangs it short and on the body. Kohli gets on his toes and looks to fend it off. It bounces extra and goes wide of the short leg off the handle. A single taken and Kohli is off the mark in a streaky manner.
A ripper to end the over, a successful one again from Archer. Just outside off on a good length, Pujara looks to defend but is beaten. Lucky not to edge behind.
Short one on middle, Kohli rides the bounce and then pulls it to short leg. The man there misfields as the ball goes to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and outside off, Pujara flays at it and gets it in the gap through point for a boundary. 50-up for India.
Short of good length around off, Pujara drops it in front of covers and gets a single.
Short and down leg, Kohli ducks under it.
Short of good length around middle, Kohli looks to drop it off the back foot towards the leg side but ends up dropping it near his boots.
Shortish and on middle, Kohli tucks it towards the man at short leg.
Floated around middle, Pujara pushes it off the front foot towards mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Pujara cuts it to deep point and scampers for a single.
Flatter and around off, Kohli pushes it to backward point now.
Some turn for Jack Leach! Tossed up around off, Kohli pushes it off the back foot through cover-point for a single.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Floated on leg, Pujara skips down the track and then whips it towards deep mid-wicket as the ball crosses the fence there.
Now, he brings a solid front foot defence on this tossed up ball around off does Pujara.
Loopy delivery on the pads first up from Bess, Kohli strokes it down to long on for a single.
On off, Pujara blocks it out to short leg.
Floated on middle, Pujara whips it to short mid-wicket.
Floated on midlde, Pujara waits for the ball to come and then turns it towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up around off, Kohli lunges froward and defends it out.
Quicker and fuller outside off, Kohli taps it down the track off the back foot.
Length and around off, Pujara plays a compact front foot defense.

Beaten! Leg cutter from Stokes and it is bowled on length too. The ball is in the channel outside off, Pujara goes to feel for the ball but gets beaten on the movement there. The ball dies down on its way to the keeper.
Good length and around off, Pujara keeps it out off the front foot.
short of good length and outside off, Pujara is watchful as he defends it to the off side.
Good length and in the channel around off, Pujara covers his sticks and lets it go though to Buttler.
A fuller length and bit away from off, Pujara has no issues in leaving it. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Anderson speed in and bowls a fuller one around off, Kohli pushes it to  covers.
Now bowls it on a length and around off, Kohli hops inside the crease and then pushes it to point.
A fuller one targetting the stumps, Kophli opens his stance then defends it to cover-point.
Length and around off, Virat comes on the front foot and then defends it to point.
Full and on the pads, Kohli flicks it through mid-wicket and gets the session rolling with a couple.
Short of good length and around off, Kohli taps it off the back foot towards point. A good first over after Lunch from Anderson.
Full and wide outside off, almost a wide yorker and Pujara sees no need to play at it.
Length and around off, Pujara guides it off the back foot towards backward point.
A nice defensive push on this length ball around off and Pujara gets a single.
Length and around middle, Kohli looks to clip it to the leg side but gets a soft leading edge towards cover-point for a single.
Full on off, Pujara gets down a bit low and then dead bats it down the track towards mid on.
Length and outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to it. Archer is nice in his groove there.
Fuller and  in that channel around off, Kohli blocks it out to point once again.
Length and outside off, Virat sees it and then decides to lift his willow to let the ball pass through.
Another one in that channel well outside off, tempting Kohli to play the drive away from the body but the Indian skipper lets it be.
Length and around off, Kohli defends it to the leg side.
Length and around off, Kohli taps it towards covers.
Once again the line is outside off from Anderson and Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Fuller and in that channel of uncertainity and Pujara covers his sticks to let the ball through.
Length and angled on off, Pujara blocks it solidly towards mid on.
Fuller once again from Jofra and Pujara pushes it from within the crease. It shaped a little bit there.
Still swing available. :Length and around off, moving away from Pujara. Cheteshwar shoulders arms to it.
Full and in the driving zone for Pujara, Cheteshwar drives it but straight to mid off.
Length and around middle, Pujara blocks it from within the crease there.
Loopy ball on middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for one by Kohli.
Floated around off, Pujara is solid in defense.
Pujara comes down the track and tucks it towards square leg for one.
Floated just outside off, Kohli lunges forward and blocks.
Flat and around off, Kohli stays back and blocks.
Flat again, it pitches around off and turns in again. Kolhi tucks it towards the man at short leg.

Sharp bouncer from Archer. This one is around the body. Pujara looks to fend it off. The ball hits the gloves and it goes wide of the man at short leg. Fielder at leg gully would've gobbled this one. A single taken.
Good length and around off and middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.

Beats the outside edge of Kohli this time. Terrific from Archer. A hint of shape away from Archer. This is pitched just outside off, Kohli gets forward and looks to defend. The ball goes away just a touch but it is enough to beat the outside edge.
Too full this time and Kohli pokes it towards point and gets to the other end.
Bangs this one short. Pujara ducks.
Good length and around off, solidly kept out.
Floated around off, Kohli lunges forward and blocks.
Flat and around off, Kohli goes back and blocks.
Shortish and around off, Kohli goes back and taps it in front of backward point for a run.
Tossed up and around off, Pujara comes down the track and flicks it through square leg for one.
On off, kept out.

In the air... just short. Risky from Kohli. Goes for the flick to this full ball without reaching to the pitch. There is a fielder at short mid-wicket, Rory Burns it is. He dives forward and looks to catch but it falls short.
Full and around off, Pujara digs it out towards point and takes off for a single. Kohli says no. Pujara returns back.
Full and around off, pushed towards covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one in the channel outside off, left alone again.
Outside off again from Anderson. This one swings late and comes in but Pujara has no issues leaving it alone.
Very full and around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Flat and around middle, Kohli is on the back foot to block.
Short again, once again Kohli stays deep in his crase. He flicks but short leg makes a half stop. No run taken.
Low full toss, it is pushed to mid on. Kohli calls for the single. Pujara responds and they get it easily.
Sharp turn. This one pitches outside off and spins in sharply. Pujara manages to get the bat down in time. It takes the inner half and hits his pad.
Full and around middle, flicked to mid on.
Full again, Pujara flicks powerfully. It is to the right of Bess who dives that side to keep it down to a dot.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, Kohli pushes it towards the cover region.
Another one in the channel outside off, Kohli makes another leave.
Outside off again, Kohli leaves again.
Wide outside off again, Kohli is not keen to play at it.
And again! Kohli is not interested at anything that is wide outside off.
Looped up on off, Pujara defends it to the on side.
Full and around off, Pujara comes on the front foot and then whips it to mid-wicket for a single.
On middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Big, big wicket for England. Bess would be on cloud nine after that wicket. A dream wicket for him. Bess tosses this one up outside off and gets it to spin into Kohli. Virat comes on the front foot and goes to defend it away from the body. The ball catches the inside edge of his bat and lobs straight to Ollie Pope at short leg. Pope there gets to the ball and holds onto it. A fine catch from him. Bess is fired up. He will remember this wicket for a long time.
On middle, clipped away to the leg side by Rahane.
Floated on middle, Rahane dead bats it near his boots. Big over in the context of the game. A brilliant over from the young Dom Bess.
Fuller length ball on the pads of Pujara, he clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full and around middle, a slight inswing there as Rahane fends it away at the last instance towards deep backward square leg. He get off the mark with a single.
Fuller and around off, Pujara is solid in defense there.
Length and around off, Pujara is rooted to his crease as he blocks it to short mid-wicket this time.
Now bowls a length ball outside off, Pujara does not play a stroke to it.
A solid defensive stroke is what Pujara is known for and he plays one on this length ball around off from Anderson.
Full and around off middle, Rahane goes for the flick but is not to the pitch of the ball as he hits it wide of Rory Burns at short mid-wicket.
On middle, clipped to short leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a stunner! Lovely catch from Root there. Bess into the game here. He first sends the captain and now the vice-captain. Tossed up around off, a bit of dip for Dom as Rahane tries to get to the pitch of the ball. He though chips it uppishly towards covers where Root put out his left hand and the ball sticks into his palm. India in all sorts of trouble with the top order back into the hut.
Full on off, Pant dead bats it right under his eyes. It would be interesting to see how he places his game here.
Floated on middle, Pant blocks it out from the crease once again.
Flatter outside off, Pant slaps it straight to short cover. Another brilliant over from Dom Bess comes to an end. A wicket-maiden from him.
Length and around off, Pujara clips it towards square leg.
Length and outside off, Pujara lifts his willow high and lets the ball go.
Another one outside off, Pujara makes a leave once again.
Fuller and outside off, Pujara shoulders arms at it once again.
On middle, clipped to short square leg.
On middle, kept out by Pujara this time.
Full on off, Pant dead bats it right under his eyes.
On middle, Pant clips it through mid-wicket. The fielder from mid-wicket chases the ball this the boundary and pulls it inside the ropes at the last instance. Pant gets off the mark with three runs.
On middle, Pujara offers his pad as a mode of defense this time.
Floated around middle, defended to the leg side .
On middle, defended to short mid-wicket off the back foot.
Fuller on middle, Pujara whips it from around his legs but straight to mid-wicket.
FOUR! On the pads on a fuller length, Pant flicks it down to the fine leg fence. Poor from Archer on the first ball.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Another poor ball from Archer. He bowls it wide outside off and it is short in length. Pant reaches out and punches it through the covers for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off, Pant drives it towards mid off.
Full and around off, Pant is solid in defense.
Full and around off, kept out.
Full and wide outside off, another fluent drive from Pant but he finds mid off.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket by Pujara.
Comes down the track again, flicks and finds mid-wicket.
Flat and spinning in. Pujara this time stays back and flicks. It is uppish but falls well short of the man at mid-wicket.
Floated outside off, Pujara comes down the track and pads it away.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Too full and Pujara drives it by coming down the track. He drives it hard through mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Pujara. A solid shot. Bess tosses it up, Pujara puts the dancing shoes on again. Makes it a full toss and drills it through mid off.

Pant shows his plans. He is not going to just block. There is a man at long on but he wants to clear him. Comes down the track and looks to go big. Mistimes it off the inner half down to long on. A single. Maybe he doesn't want Leach to settle.
Full and just outside off, driven wide of mid off by Pujara for a single.
Big turn! Short and outside off, spins in. Pujara stays back and looks to defend. Inside edge, on the pad and it lobs. Buttler tries to catch but it drops away.

SIX! There goes Pant! He doesn't care if you have a long on in place. Backs himself, comes down the track and Leach tosses it up and around off. Pant nails the slog over long on for a biggie. 100 up for India.

SIX! And again! This time it wasn't too far away from the fielder there. Tossed up again from Leach. Pant comes down the track again. This time he is not to the pitch but goes with the shot. Fails to middle it but it is good enough to clear the fielder at deep mid-wicket. Lawrence tried to catch to his left but it goes away and over the fence.
Gets down and sweeps it down to deep square leg for one. 15 from the over.
Tossed up and outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Floated on off, Pant defends it with  straight bat.
Flatter and outside off, slapped towards deep cover for a single.
Fuller on off, Pujara goes on the back foot and defends it somehow.
On middle, punched off the back foot towards the leg side.
Floated on off and middle, Pujara looks to defend it but ekes out an inside edge which drops in front of Ollie Pope at short leg. Another excellent over from Bess there.
SIX! Take that! This is some confidence from Pant. Leach shows courage and tosses it up and around off, Pant accepts the offer, dances down the track and powers it over long on for a biggie.
Short and around middle, tucked away to deep square leg for one.
Short and wide, spinning away. Pujara guides it through short third man. The ball races to the fence. The fielder chases it down and saves one. Three taken.
Short and on middle and leg, clipped through square leg for one.
Tossed up and outside off, poked towards point.
Tossed up and just outside off, spins away. Left alone.
Floated around off, pushed to mid off.
Tossed up and outside off, driven to the right of the cover fielder who dives to his right and stops.
Darted around off, a bit shortish length. Pant goes back to block.
Short and around off, kept out.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed wide of the point fielder for one.
Short and just around off, Pujara looks to pull but mistimes it towards mid-wicket.

SIX! Up and over! This man is just unbelievable. They have 5 men catching in the deep but Pant doesn't care. And Leach continues to teases him. Pant is down the track again. Goes for the shot. Clears Archer at long on who tries to catch but it goes over him. 4th six for Pant. A quick-fire 50-run stand comes up between these two.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards mid off for one.
Flat and around middle, clipped to mid on for one.
Flat and just outside off, poked towards point for one.
Floated around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Flat and just outside off, left alone. 4-0-41-0. He has been taken to the cleaners by Pant.
Outside off, left alone.
Quicker one on the pads, tucked towards fine leg for one.

NOT OUT! Pujara is safe on both the front. They check if it is bump ball first. Pujara is safe there and then comes the run out. He is back in with a dive. Floated around off and middle, Pujara comes down the track and flicks. Pope stops the ball to his left and throws the ball to the keeper. Buttler takes the bails off. An appeal is made. It is for a catch as well. The umpires get together. The soft signal for the catch is not out. Replays show that the ball is clearly bounced. Also, they now check the run out. Pujara is in. Direct hit would've been the end of Pujara.
Full and around middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
On middle, pushed to mid on this time.
Tossed up and around middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket for one.
On middle, whipped away towards fine leg. Sibley theremops it up as the batsmen take a brace.
Flatter and outside off, Pujara slaps it towards third man. Bess now cuts it off. A couple once again.
Flatter around off, Pujara pushes it to point there.
Floated on off, kept out.

FOUR! Beautifully placed! Brilliant piece of timing on it! Tossed up around middle, Pujara skips down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a boundary. Leach trying to stem the run flow from his end.
On off, dabbed towards short third man. Looks for a single does Pujara but is sent back by Pant.
FOUR! Lofted away! It's Bess' turn to take the beating now. Tossed up around off, Pant goes inside out and just clears the man there for a boundary.
Full and straight outside off, Pant lets it be.
Tossed up around off, Pant comes on the front foot and then defends it. He trusts the ball that it won't come into him.
Full on off, pushed straight to short cover.
Another tossed up ball going straight with the angle, Pant leaves it for Buttler.
Sharp spin there! Tossed up outside off, the ball spins away after pitching and Pant has not fuss in leaving it. England playing with Pant's patience. Can they scalp him before Tea?

FOUR! 50 for Pujara! His 29th in Tests! 4th in his last 5 innings. Tossed up around off, Pujara gets to the pitch of the ball and then drives it through covers for a boundary to get to his milestone. What a time to get to it with the team in trouble. He needs to play a long inning.
Round the wicket now to Pujara and he pads it away.
Flatter outside off, Pujara cuts it to point for a single.
Full on middle, clipped to mid-wicket. A rare sight from Pant there.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR PANT! A brilliant counter-attack from him. He has come like a flash here in the middle. He took Leach on as soon as he came to bowl and has raced to a half ton. Just 40 balls to get to his 5th half ton. What an innings from him so far. Leach tosses it wide outside off, Pant dances down and thumps it through mid off.
Tossed up on off, Pant gets to the pitch of the ball and then strokes it to long on for a single.
Tossed up outside off, driven to covers.
Tossed up around off, Pant defends it out off the front foot.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for a single.
Tossed up on off, spinning into Pujara, he turns it to short leg.
Full and around off, Pujara comes down the track and pushes it to the  right of Bess. Dom runs to that side and fields it.
Tossed up on off, Pujara dead bats it to the leg side .THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Good length and around off, Pant blocks.
Around off on a good length, Pant defends solidly again.
Fuller and around off, kept out by Pant.
Slipped down the leg side on a fuller length. Pant flicks it to fine leg for one.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on middle, it is flicked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! THUMP! Short and wide outside off to begin from Anderson. Pant is quick to pounce on it. He flays it through cover-point for a boundary.
Fuller and around middle and leg, kept out.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Good length and around off, Pant looks to defend. A hint of shape away. Just a hint. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to gully.
FOUR! Second boundary in the over. Pant continues to find the fence. Short and wide outside, Pant punches it on the up and through the covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Glorious from Pujara now! Full toss from Archer. Pujara drives it through mid on and it races away to the fence.
Short and wide outside off, Pujara looks to punch but mistimes it towards the cover region.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Shortish and around off, Pujara taps it on the off side.
Outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Shortish and around off, kept out by Pujara

FOUR! Nicely done! A good length ball outside off, Pant looks to defend. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes between the slip and gully fielder. Races to the fence. Credit to Pant for playing it with soft hands.
Good length and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Pant drives it towards mid off and calls for the single. He takes off but Puajra shouts loud no.
Good length and around off, Pant taps it towards cover for one.
Back of a length and just outside off, poked towards point.

Ouch! That's on the gloves. Pujara is in visible pain. He won't flinch though. He is got hit so many times on his body during India's tour to Australia. He got bruised but he continued the battle. And he will look to do so. Coming to the ball, this one pitches around off, it jags back in. A bit of extra bounce as well. Pujara looks to defend but the ball hits his gloves and goes on the leg side.
Back of a length and angled in, Pant keeps it out.
Back of a length and on middle, worked on the leg side.
Banged short but down the leg side. Goes further away. Pant lets it be. Buttler does well to move to his right and collect.
Fullish and outside off, Pant looks to drive it hard. Mistimes it just wide of the cover fielder. A half stop but they don't go for the run.
Banged short and on middle, kept out.
Firm drive! A fuller ball, outside off. Pant drives it well but finds mid off.
Tossed up and around off, Pujara dances down the track, converts it to full toss and drives but finds mid on.
Full and around off, flicked to mid-wicket this time.
Floated around off, Pujara comes down the track and blocks.
FOUR! Slammed away! Short ball, around off, Pujara rocks back and nails the pull over square leg for a boundary. 100-run stand is up between the two.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Full and around off, Pujara dances down the track and flicks wide of the man at mid on. Quick single.
Length and around off, Pujara plays if off the back foot now.
FOUR! Punched away! Short and around off, Pujara punches it off the back foot and in front of square for a boundary at covers.
Full on off, pushed to covers from within the crease.
Short of good length and around off, Pujara drops it towards point and scampers for a single this time.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and down leg, Pant makes a leave.
Tossed up on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter outside off, slapped through covers for a single.
On middle, Pujara clips it off the front foot towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Excellent use of feet! Tossed up around off, Pujara uses the feet to get to the pitch of the ball to nail the drive towards covers for a boundary.
Tossed up outside off, Pujara comes on the front foot and tries to defend it with his bat-pad to gether. The ball goes off his pads towards the off side.
Tossed up on middle, Pujara clips it to short leg.
Short on off, Pant flays it away through covers for a single.
Full on middle, clipped to mid-wicket.
Fuller on middle, blocked off the front foot.
On off, Pujara plays it to covers for a single.
Full on off, Pujara drives it down to long on but Root from mid on runs behind it and saves a couple of runs.
Full and outside off, Pant plays it to point.
Full and outside off, turned towards mid-wicket.
Quicker and pushed through outside off, Pujara plays it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Pujara dances down the track to defend but gets in a tangle there.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pujara falls! In a very unfortunate manner though. He is livid with himself. A rank long hop. Pujara rocks back and goes for the pull. He connects it well. But hang on. England are celebrating. Burns catches it. What happened there? He nailed the pull. But the ball hits the back of Ollie Pope at shrot leg who is ducking to save himself. The ball hits his back and lobs to Burns at mid-wicket. This wicket is pretty similar to one India lost in 2001 at the Wankhede. It was SRT then who got out in a similar manner. He went for the pull to the poor ball by Mark Waugh. Tendulkar connected the pull really well but the ball hit ducking Langer, the current Australia coach, and went wide of Ponting who was at mid-wicket. Punter ran to his right and pull off a fine catch with a dive forward. He was unfortunate then, and Pujara now.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Tossed up on middle, pushed to covers.
Darted outside off, Pant looks to pad it away. It spins away.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Floated around off, blocked.
FOUR! There goes Pant. He doesn't go down the ground but goes to innovative way. Tossed up and on middle, Pant moves inside the crease and paddles it over the leg gully fielder. A boundary.
Flat and around off, kept out this time.

SIX! And Pant proves everyone wrong again. The ones who thought that he may not go for the big hit after losing his partner. Leach tosses it up and outside off, Pant dances down the track and powers it over long on for a massive six. He is into the 80s now. 200 up for the Indians.
Loopy ball around off, kept out.
Low full toss, pushed to mid off.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler by Sundar.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to the man at covers.
Floted around off, Sundar is solid in defense.
Good leave! Bess floats this outside off, Sundar comes on the front foot and shoulders arms.
In the air... safe! Tossed up and outside off, Pant looks to slog sweep. Ends up getting a top edge and the ball goes over the slip cordon. It goes to fine leg and they take three.
Floated around off, kept out.
FOUR! Sundar is up and running! Tossed up and just outside off, Sundar nails the drive through the covers for a boundary.
Shortish and around off, spins in. Tucked towards mid-wicket.
Flat and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Short and just around off, turns in. Sundar works it towards mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! BOOM! Sundar nails the drive through mid on. A fuller ball around middle, Sundar drills it through mid on for a boundary.
Drives nicely again but this time he finds the cover fielder.
FOUR! Cut away! Another boundary for Sundar. Short and wide outside off, Sundar goes back and slaps it through point. Finds the fence.
Tossed up and around off, pushed to mid off.
Tossed up and outside off, hit to sweeper cover for a single.
Short and on middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket for one. A good over for the Indians. 9 off the over.
Tossed up and outside off, Pant leaves it alone.
Another one darted outside off, left alone.
Another one wide outside off, Pant once again lets it be.
And again! Good from Root too. He is teasing Pant here but Pant is not going after him.
Loopy again, this one is pushed towards covers.
Goes after this one and drives it wide of long off for one.
FOUR! Pant is into the 90s now! A full toss on middle, Pant gets down and pulls it over square leg for a boundary.
Floated around off, kept out.
Very full, pushed to mid off.

OUT! TAKEN! Bess gets his man. Pant falls. Kohli looking tensed in the dressing room. Big wicket. Floated outside off, Pant dances down the track and looks to go big over extra cover. The ball though spins away. He ends up slicing it high in the air towards extra cover. Leach there comes forward and does well to take the catch. End of a fine counter-attacking knock form Rishabh. Pant lives by the sword and he dies by the same. He got to the 90s in this fashion and once again falls. 4th time in his Test career he has gone for 90.
Tossed up on off, Ashwin comes on the front foot and blocks it out.
Fuller on off, Ashwin strokes it gently to mid on. Another good over for Bess.
Tossed up on middle, tucked away towards fine leg and past leg gully for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Ashwin lets it be.
Flatter and outside off, Ashwin cuts it to deep cover for a single. Ashwin gets off the mark.
Tossed up around off, Sundar defends it to the off side.
Flatter on off, Sundar drops it wide of short leg now.
Tossed up on middle, Sundar gets in an awkward position as he fends it to the leg side.
Tossed up around off, Ashwin looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire.
On middle, Ashwin blocks it from his crease.
On middle, defended to the leg side.
Flighted on off, Ashwin keeps it out watchfully.
On off, Ashwin comes on the front foot and then defends it.
On off, kept out.
Full and wide outside off, Sundar lets it be.
Full and around middle, pushed through mid on.
Flat and around off, Ashwin pokes it towards point.
Tossed up and outside off, turning away. Left alone.
Tossed up and wide outside off, Ashwin drives but the cover fielder knocks it down to his left.
Full and around off, driven left again and the cover fielder cannot do anything. A single.
Flat and around off, Ashwin goes back to block.
Floated around off, kept out.
Tossed up and around off, Ashwin is solid in defense.
Short and on middle, tucked towards the leg side for one.
Full on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Tossed up outside off, Sundar leaves it.
Flatter and outside off, punched off the back foot towards deep cover  for a single.
On middle, clipped to square leg for a single by Sundar.
Tossed up outside off, Ashwin lets it be.
Floated on off, Ashwin prods forward and defends it.
Flatter and outside off, Ashwin cuts it through point now and crosses ends with Sundar.
On off, kept out by Sundar.
Length and outside off, Ashwin makes a leave now. India still have 15 overs to survive the day.
Lovely delivery! Length and outside off, Ashwin looks to poke at it off the back foot but the slightest of shape there means the outside edge is not found.
Length and around middle, clipped towards the leg side for a single.
Fuller and angled into middle, clipped to deep square leg for a single. It though went off the pads. Leg bye given.
Full on off, Ashwin defends it out.
Short of good length and around off, Ashwin hops and defends it out onto the track.
Floated on off, Sundar defends it off the front foot. The ball goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Sundar survives! Nicely looped up ball outside off, Sundar does not offer bat but puts his pad in the line of the ball and get rapped there. A pretty optimistic appeal from Leach there but nothing from the umpire.  Jack convinces his skipper to take the review and Root signals 'T'. As there was not shot offered directly the Ball Tracker comes on and it shows that the ball was going well over the stumps there. England just tried to take a chance there with 3 reviews at their disposal.
Full and around off, pushed down to mid on for a quick single.
Floated around off, turns away. Watchfully left alone.
Tossed up and outside off, driven towards point.
Full and around off, kept out.
In the channel outside off, Sundar lets it be.
Length and outside off, Sundar lets it go through to the keeper there.
Another fuller and outside off, Sundar does offer a stroke to it.
Length and around off, Sundar defends it to mid on now.
Short of good length and around off, Sundar pulls it towards square leg for a single.
Short of good length and outside off, Ashwin defends it off the back foot and towards the bowler.

NOT OUT! Sundar survives once again! Tossed up ball spinning into Sundar who makes a leave to getrapped on the pads. There is an appeal and the umpire does not move. England take the review and the replays come in. Once again no shot offered so we move to the Ball Tracker. Once again the ball is bouncing over the stumps there.
Full on off, driven back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, spinning into Sundar, he misses his defensive push to get rapped high on the pads.
On off, kept out off the front foot.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards the off side off the front foot.
On middle, kept out.
Banged short and around middle, Ashwin sits under it.
Good length and just outside off, poked towards the point region.
Length and just outside off, poked towards point.
Fuller and outside off, poked towards gully for one.
Low full toss, flicked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Classy from Sundar! A fullish ball outside off, Sundar punches this one the up through the covers and it races to the right of the man at mid off. Super shot to end the over.
Full and around off, pushed towards covers.
Flat and around off, poked towards point this time.
Flat and just outside off, Ashwin punches it towards the cover region for a run.
Floated outside off, Sundar looks to defend but the ball spins in. The ball hits his gloves and then the body. Drops safely on the off side.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Short and around off, turns in, tucked towards square leg for a single.
Low full toss, punched back to the bowler.
Floated around off, pushed towards cover region.
Tossed up and on middle, kept out.
Full toss outside off, pushed to mid off for nothing.
Short and wide outside off, cut to point for one.
Flat and around off, kept out.

DROPPED! Oh, dear! Archer misses a chance! That was a no-look shot from Sundar, by the look of it. He goes for the slog sweep but the ball goes off the toe end. It goes high in the air towards long on. Archer from mid on runs behind and tries to catch. He gets both hands but it spills out.
On off, kept out.
Floated outside off, Sundar pads it away.
Tossed up and around off, turns in. Sundar keeps it out.
Spins in again from shortish length. Sundar goes back to block. Ashwin wanted the single but Sundar sends him back.
Tossed up and around off, pushed to mid on for nothing.
Tossed up and outside off, driven to mid off for nothing.
Quicker and pushed through on off, pushed off the back foot to covers.
Flatter and around off, Ashwin dabs it to point.
On middle and leg, tucked to short leg.
Flatter on off, Ashwin pushes it back to mid on.
Full on middle, Ashwin turns it to the leg side this time.
FOUR! Through the gap! Tossed up and outside off, Sundar goes for the drive against the turn and creams it through covers for a boundary. 250 comes up for India.
Spinning on middle, turned to square leg for a single.
On off, Ashwin defends it out.
Floated outside off, left alone by Ashwin.
On off, pushed down the track there.
Floated around off, Ashwin defends it off the front foot to see off the over from Leach.
Full and going down leg, Sundar flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length and outside off, Ashwin defends it to covers.
Short of good length and around off, Ashwin hops and defends it right under his boots.
Full and around off, Ashwin pushes it to mid off.
Length and around off, pushed to covers by Ashwin.
Short of good length outside off, Ashwin drops his wrists and lets the ball through.
Tossed up outside off, spinning into Sundar. Washington makes a leave.
Full outside off, defended off the front foot.
Tossed up and turning into middle, Siundar plays it to the leg side.

OHH! Drama there! Just evades the leg stump! Tossed up and off, spinning into Sundar, Washington defends it as the ball goes between his leg and to the right of the keeper. Buttler does well to collect it.
FOUR BYES! Massive turn there! Tossed up around off, Sundar looks to tuck it to the leg side but the ball spins away from him and past the keeper into the fine leg fence. Byes signalled.
On off, kept out by Siundar. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Bess starts off with a floated delivery on middle and leg, Ashwin tucks this one to the square leg region.
Floated and on off, Ashwin keeps this one out.
Tossed up and around off, Ashwin is solid in his defense.
Ashwin shows off his front foot defense on this occasion.
First runs of the morning. Short and on middle, spinning into the right-hander, Ashwin flicks this one to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! SHOT! Sundar starts off well. Fractionally short and outside the off pole, Sundar's eyes light up seeing the width and he camps back and slams this one through the cover region for a boundary.
Flighted and on middle, Ashwin keeps this one out.
Identical to the last delivery, Ashwin offers a solid defense again.
On off, played towards covers.
Floats it up and lands it on the middle pole this time, Ashwin pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and floated outside off, Ashwin looks to cut this one but the ball stays a touch low and goes under Ash's bat into Buttler's mitts.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
FOUR! A loosener and Sundar does not miss out. He moves into the 40s as well. A full toss on off, Sundar bunts this one through mid on and downtown into the ropes.
On off, kept out.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Flat, outside off, punched to covers for a quick single.
Gets his bat across and keeps this one out well.

SIX! WOAH! That came out of nowhere, from Ashwin. Great use of the feet. Bess floats this one up and lands it just around the off pole, Ashwin skips down the track and bangs this one over the wide long on fence for the first biggie of the day.
Loopy and on off, Sundar prods forward and blocks it out.
On middle and leg, Sundar flicks this one to square leg for a single.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards point.
Ashwin blocks this one with a straight bat towards the mid on region.
On middle, defended by Ash. One run of the over.

FOUR! Short again and Sundar latches onto this one. Flatter and outside off, Sundar camps back and slaps this one through the cover region again. Finds the ropes. Sundar moves onto 47 now. This also brings up the 50-run stand between these two.
Sundar has just watchfully blocked this out.
Tossed up and on middle, Sundar comes forward and defends.
Short, outside off, pushed to point.
Flighted on middle, Sundar works this one back to the bowler.
Full toss on middle, bunted down to long on for a single.

FIFTY FOR WASHINGTON SUNDAR! His second in as many Tests. He showed his batting abilities in his debut Test in Australia and now he has continued to enhance his reputation in Test match cricket as a batter. Flighted delivery wide outside off, Sundar leans forward and plays a beautiful drive through cover for a boundary to bring up his milestone. The dressing room is on its feet to applaud the youngster's knock. The job is not done though and he will look to stay in the middle for as long as possible.
