Tossed up on off, Sundar pads this one away to the off side. An appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Flighted on off, Sundar comes down and works this to mid on for a single.
Floated on off, RA pushes this to covers.
On off, Ashwin plays this to point.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Bowls a good length ball outside off, stays low as Sundar does not bother to offer a stroke to this one.
Another length ball outside off, Sundar lets it be.
Outside off, left alone for Buttler to collect.
Fourth time lucky? Nahhhh! Another good length ball outside off, Sundar again is not interested in playing at this one.
Short of a length ball on off, Sundar blocks this one to the point region.
Maiden for Anderson to start off with. This is in that channel outside off, Sundar leaves it alone.
Archer bowls a fuller one on off, Ashwin pushes it back to Jofra, who stops it with his boot.
Good length and around off, pushed through point for a single.

FOUR! This is brilliant strokeplay. Kohli will want ask Sundar how he plays these shots, by the looks of it. Archer comes 'round the wicket and bowls a good length ball on off, Sundar drives this one through mid on and there is no reason for anyone to chase after this. Runs away to the ropes.
Bowls a back of a length ball on off, Sundar looks to block but the bounce gets slightly more as it hits him on the bat's handle.
Slips this one down the leg side, Sundar leaves it be.
Short of a length and on middle, Sundar blocks this one to the leg side. 5 runs off Jofra's first over of the morning.
On a good length and on off, Ashwin plays this one to mid on.
Around off on a good length, Ash plays this one towards point this time.
On a good length and outside off this time, Ashwin leaves it alone.
Short of a length this time and just around the off pole, Ashwin punches this one to covers.
FOUR! CRACKED! Lovely stroke. Jimmy bowls a good length delivery just around off, enticing Ashwin for the drive. Ravichandran acceps this offer and creams this one through covers.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Washington defends this one with a straight bat back towards Jofra.
Goes fuller and on the middle pole, Sundar whips this one through mid-wicket for a single. Could have been two but they settle just for the single. The partnership moves to 69 runs off 160 balls now.
Around off on a length, kept out by Ravichandran.

FOUR! Another beautiful stroke by Ashwin. Jofra goes for a length ball outside off, room to play with and Ashwin leans into this one and drives it wonderfully through the covers. Getting into this stride now, is Ravichandran.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On a length around off and middle, RA plays this one to mid on.
Anderson goes for a fuller one outside the off pole, Sundar lets this one through.
Similar to the previous delivery, left alone.
Outside off on a length, Sundar offers no shot to this one.
Length and outside off, another leave by Washington.
Another length ball in that fourth stump channel, no shot offered this time.
Good length and on middle, whipped to the mid on region.
On the middle pole on a good length, Ashwin clips this one through mid-wicket for a brace this time. 300 up for India as well.

EDGY FOUR. No one there and it runs away to the ropes. A back of a length and on middle and off, Ashwin looks for the tuck away to the leg side but the ball takes the outside edge and goes in between the gap at first slip and gully and into the third man fence.
Good length and on middle, whipped through the mid-wicket region for a single now.
Blocked to the cover region this time.
Slightly behind the good length and on the off pole, WS hops and defends this one out.
Bumper on middle and leg, Sundar leaves it alone.
Flighted on middle, Ashwin pushes it to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! The decision to bring on Leach has paid rich dividends for England. He strikes on the second ball and this stand which will troubling England so much has been broken. The extra bounce has done the trick. Flighted and on off, bounces more than what Ashwin expected probably. He prods forward and looks to defend but the ball takes the top half of the bat and lobs to the right of Ashwin. Stokes and Buttler both run towards the ball but Buttler is the one who runs and gobbles this one up. Ashwin stands for a few seconds and then starts walking back. First success of the morning for the English Lions. India trail by 273 runs.
Flighted on leg, tucked to the leg side.
Floated on middle, worked to the square leg region.
Flighted and around off, Nadeem works this one to the mid off region.
Tossed up and on middle, Shahbaz looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes to the point region.
Bowls a good length ball outside off, stays very low this time, as Sundar lets this one go. Buttler stops this one well.
Back of a length and outside off, Sundar punches this one to the cover region.
Short of a length and around off, WS blocks.
Outside off on a length, Sundar slaps this one to the point fielder again. Does not opt for the single on this occasion though.
BEAUTYYYY! Things are starting to happen for both Leach and Archer. On a good length and around off, nips away slightly as Sundar looks to block. Zips past the outside edge and to Buttler.

A quick single. On a good length and on middle, Sundar clips this one to the mid-wicket region for a very quick run. The fielder there collects and has a shy at the striker's end but he ends up hitting Nadeem. Also, a no ball as Jofra had overstepped.
Goes for the yorker but ends up bowling a full toss down the leg side, Nadeem looks to flick but misses. A wry smile on Archer's face after this one. 2 off this over.
Floated around off, Washington Sundar pushes it to mid on.
Flighted outside off, Sundar pads it away. Appeal from the English players but nothing from the umpire.
Tossed up on off, Sundar defends it.
Darted fuller on off, Washington Sundar milks it to long on for a run.
Shorter outside off, Nadeem defends it off his back foot.
Darted too full on middle. Gives the ball no chance to spin. Nadeem taps it to the right of Leach.
FOUR! Nicely played! Slightly shorter around off, the ball keeps a bit low. Sundar adjusts well and just guides it away from slips for a boundary.
Short ball! Sundar ducks under it.
Edged but does not carry! Good length ball around off, the ball keeps low this time. Sundar looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge but it falls well, well short of Stokes at first slip.
On off, Sundar keeps it out.
Short but down the leg side. Sundar ducks.
Another one down the leg side, Sundar looks to flick but misses.
Floated on off, Nadeem defends it.
Flighted on off, Nadeem keeps it out and away from silly point.
Floated on middle, Nadeem blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Nadeem blocks it uppishly. Lawrence at silly point is a bit away on the right. Had he been at traditional silly point, this could have been the end of Nadeem.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nadeem departs and Leach gets his second of the day. What a difference a day makes! He was hammered left, right, and center by Pant on Day 3 but today Leach has been fantastic and gets another one. Slightly shorter on off, not too short just a tad. Nadeem gets on his back foot to defend but the ball turns away and takes the outside edge.  It just about carries to first slip and Stokes there manages to take a good catch. The extra man at silly point made him uncomfortable.
Floated on middle, Ishant starts his innings with a solid block.
Good length ball outside off, Sundar dabs this one towards the gully region.
PLAY AND A MISS! Sundar goes after this one but misses it. On a good length and outside off, Sundar looks to drive this one away but he misses his stroke completely.
BEATEN! Another great ball by Sundar. On a good length again and just around off, Sundar looks for the defensive push away but he does not connect bat with ball.
Another delivery which is on a good length and outside the off pole, Sundar again looks to push this one away but he does not make any connection.
Sundar is not getting it to connect well. Length and outside off, Sundar looks to drive this one away but again fails to get any bat on this one.

SIX! Dear, oh dear! Taken the aerial route, has Sundar. Moves into the 70s with his shot as well. Anderson bowls this one a good length and just around off, Sundar slams this one over the bowler's head and downtown for a biggie.
Flighted on middle, Ishant uses his long stride and blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Ishant defends it.
FOUR! Ishant getting aggressive now. A shot that has come out of the blue. Floated on middle, Sharma sweeps it in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Flighted on middle, Sharma blocks it.
Short and spinning away outside off. Ishant shows great awareness and offers a good leave.
Tossed up on off and middle, Ishant keeps it out.
Good shot! Length ball around off, Sundar punches it to deep point for one.
Edged but safe! Fuller on off, Ishant looks to defend but gets an outside edge which goes to Burns at gully on a bounce.
Full on off, Ishant flicks it on the bounce to short leg.
Full on off, Ishant taps it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! James Anderson gets his first wicket of the game and Ishant's fight comes to an end. Excellent bowling from Anderson. Sets up the Indian tailender brilliantly. Full ball, followed by another full ball, puts Ishant on the front foot. Then Anderson unleashes a short ball. It is well-directed and more importantly, the ball does raise off the surface. Not an easy thing to do on a subcontinental Day 4 pitch. It is a cross-seam delivery. Ishant awkwardly plays at it and ends up giving a dolly to short leg. Ollie Pope there takes a simple catch. Indians need 56 runs to avoid the follow-on.
Full on off, Bumrah manages to defend it.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Sundar will look to be aggressive now as he knows he is batting with a number 11. Floated outside off, Sundar goes aerial over extra cover and gets a boundary.
Good running! Flighted wide outside off, Sundar drives but he gets an inside edge which sees the ball go past the stumps. He calls for two and the pair is quick between the wickets and they get it.
SIX! Smoked! Into the 80s now! Tossed up on off and middle, Sundar goes over Root's head and gets a biggie.
Flatter wide outside off, Sundar cuts it but straight to backward point.
Short and wide outside off, it spins a lot. Sundar leaves it alone.

Good running and good over for India. Sundar manages to keep the strike and keep Bumrah away from the firing line. Darted full on the pads. A puff of dust pops off the pitch. Sundar taps it to the left of the bowler and takes a quick run.
Length ball on the pads, Sundar flicks it to square leg.
On middle, coming in with the angle. Sundar defends it to mid on with the angle.
Good length ball on off and middle, Washington defends it to the off side.
Good shot and they take a run. Length ball around off, Sundar punches it to deep point and decides to take a run. 2 balls for Bumrah to face in this over.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! What a stunning catch from Ben Stokes at first slip. Bumrah is unable to negotiate the two balls he was tasked to and India are bowled out. Fabulous catch from Stokes. Anderson bowls a full ball on off, the ball shapes away from Bumrah. Jasprit Bumrah looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge and it flies low to the right of first slip. Stokes there dives and takes a brilliant one-handed catch. INDIA BOWLED OUT FOR 337! Trail by 241!

OUT! CAUGHT! Joy for India as Ashwin starts the third innings with a wicket of the first ball. The ploy to open the bowling with Ashwin has worked superbly for India.  Brilliant start to the innings if you are an Indian fan, terrible if you are an England fan. Ashwin starts with a floated delivery on off, Burns looks to defend but he gets a thick outside edge which goes to the left of Rahane at first slip. The Indian Test vice-captain moves to that side and takes a very good catch.
Tossed up on off, Lawrence defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Lawrence keeps it out.
On the pads, Lawrence glances it to square leg.
Down the leg side, Lawrence looks to flick but misses.
Excellent start for Ashwin and India. They begin with a wicket maiden. On middle and leg, Lawrence flicks it to short leg on the bounce.
Flighted outside off. There is turn and bounce, Sibley leaves it alone.
Flighted on off, Sibley defends it off his front foot.

Turn, bounce, and a very good take from Pant. Nadeem tosses this up around off, Sibley looks to defend but the ball turns away and bounces. It goes past the outside edge of Sibley's bat. Pant behind the stumps does well to take it.
Flighted on off, Sibley keeps it out.
NO BALL! Shorter on off, Sibley punches it but it hits silly point on the bounce. Nadeem has overstepped and England get their first run of the innings.
Tossed up on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Floated outside off, Sibley keeps his eyes on the ball and leaves it alone. That will be the end of the first session. Lunch on Day 4!
FOUR! A good start to the seond session for England! Floated and on middle, Lawrence clips this one to the deep mid-wicekt region and the ball speeds away to the ropes this time.

An appeal for lbw but turned down. Floated and on off and middle, spins into the right-hander as Lawrence looks to flick but misses it and gets rapped on the pads. An appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Kohli is pondering taking the review on this occasion but he decides not to. A good decision as this woud have been going down the leg pole.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.
Another full and floated ball on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and outside off, Dan looks to work this one to the off side but he misses the shot completely.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted outside off, Sibley leaves it be.
Flighted on off, Sibley pushes this one to the cover region and the batters sneak in a quick single.
Tossed up and on off, Dan pushes this one to mid-wicket.
Flat, outside off, cut to the point region.
Full and flighted on middle, Lawrence comes down the track and flicks this one to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up and on off, Sibley strokes this one to covers for another single.
Flatter and on off, Sibley blocks this one to the mid-wicket region. The iconic chatter from Pant is going on. 'BOWLING ASH, BOWLING ASHHHH' is heard from the young wicketkeeper.
On middle, Sibley looks to block this one but the ball takes the inner half of the blade and goes to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
On middle again, tucked to mid-wicket, but straight to the fielder there.
Full and tossed up on middle, DS clips this one to deep square leg for one.
Flighted on off, Lawrence comes down the track, probably to negate the spin but he fails to connect bat with ball on this occasion and the ball takes the pads and goes to the off side.
Sibley prods forward and blocks.
Does what he did on the last ball again, does Sibley.
FOUR! Some width on offer and Sibley is not going to leave this one unpunished! Flatter and outside off, Sibley slams this one through the cover region and the ball runs away to the ropes.
On off, DS looks to block but the ball takes the inner half and goes to the leg side.
Short and outside off, punched to deep point for a single.
Goes fuller and on off, Lawrence is able to come ahead and defend this with a straight blade.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket.
On off, worked to the mid-wicket again.
Full and flighted around off, Sibley flicks this one to mid-wicket and Kohli does well to stop this one. One run.

NOT OUT! Lawrence survives. Impact was outside off. Flighted around off, spins back into the right-hander as Lawrence looks to block this one but misses and gets rapped on the pads. An appeal but nothing from the umpire. Ashwin, Kohli and Pant have a discussion. Pant is heard saying in Hindi that the ball spun a lot on this occasion. With just one second on the timer, Kohli makes the 'T' symbol. The front foot was fine on this occasion and so Ultra Edge is called for. No spike and the Ball Tracker is the next thing on the agenda. The impact is deemed to be outside off and hence, the on-field decision will also stay on. India lose a review though.
NO BALL! Ashwin has overstepped and hence, will be a no ball. Floated on off, driven to covers for a single.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Short outside off, Lawrence punches it to the right of point. Sundar fumbles and they take a single.
Flighted around off, Sibley gets on his front foot anfd blocks it.
Darted fuller on middle, Sibley defends it to the on side.
Shorter on middle, Sibley defends it to mid on.
Flighted on middle and off, Sibley takes a stride forward and defends it.
Floated on the stumps, Sibley keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Dan blocks.
Root's favorite shot is out against spinners, even though he is not out in the middle. Tossed up and around off, Lawrence gets on his knees and sweeps this one to the fine leg region for a couple.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Short and on the stumps, kept out.
Lawrence goes on his back foot and flicks this one to square leg for a single.
Around off, tapped to point this time.
Turn and bounce again from Nadeem this time. Shortish and around off, spins away and also bounces a tad bit more as Lawrence looks to have a go at this. Misses and Pant does well to collect this.
Flat, outside off, punched to the off side for one.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Flighted and around off, Sibley taps this one towards point for a single.
Loopy and around off, Dan comes ahead and drives this one to the left of the mid off fielder for one more run.
Outside off, left alone. Another no ball from Nadeem. Needs to be better on this aspect.
Full and tossed up outside off, Sibley looks to drive this one but he does not connect bat with ball on this occasion.
Floated on middle, whipped to short mid-wicket.
On middle, blocked to the leg side again.
Full and on middle, Lawrence pushes this one back to the bowler. 'NICE AREAS ASHHHHH', is what Pant is heard saying. Safe to say, he is enjoying himself out there.
On off, tapped to point for a very quick run.
FOUR! Quite full and Sibley sends this one to the ropes. Flighted and on the leg pole, SIbley sweeps this one to the fine leg region and the ball speeds away to the ropes.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ashwin gets another one and Sibley's stay out in the middle comes to an end. India has again done well to snare a wicket at the right time. Looks to defend but the ball spins just enough to induce the inside edge. Ashwin has been rewarded for his great bowling with another wicket. Bowls this one a lot straighter and on the stumps, but gets the ball to spin into the right-hander, Sibley prods forward, thinking that he can defend this one out. The ball though does enough to take the inside edge and go to the leg slip, where Pujara does well to take this one nicely. England are technically at 273 for 2 at the moment.
Floated on off, Lawrence keeps it out.
Short around off, Lawrence punches it to sweeper cover and takes a single to stretch the lead to 274!
Short outside off, Root starts his innings with a punch but to the man at cover.

FOUR! Root is off the mark in style! Good shot from Root. It has taken him just two balls to bring out the sweep. Loopy ball very full around off, Root sweeps it through mid-wicket all along the ground for a boundary.
Flighted on off, Root defends it to point.
FOUR! Another sweep and another boundary for Root. The England Test skipper is in magnificent touch. Floated on off, Root sweeps it well in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Flighted and on off, kept out.
Short and outside off, Lawrence looks to slap this one through the off side but he fails to get any bat on this one.
On middle, kept out.
Loopy and on off, Dan blocks this one out well.
Full and floated on middle, Dan eases this one through mid on for a single.
Shimmies down the track to this full ball around off and works this one to long on again for one. Root keeps the strike with this single.
Ishant starts off with a good length ball around off, nipping back in slightly after hitting the deck as Root flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, Joe flicks this one to the deep square leg region for a single.
Another good length ball on off, Lawrence works this one with the inner half of the blade towards the mid on region.
Identical to the last delivery by Sharma and Lawrence plays a similar shot this time around to mid on again.
In that channel of uncertainty outside the off pole, Lawrence just lets this one through to the keeper.
On a good length and on off, Dan pushes this one to the cover region for a single.
Flighted and on middle, Lawrence sweeps this one to deep square leg where Ishant is stationed. Catch is the call but the ball does not caryy. One run.
FOUR! Root absolutely nailed this one. Full and floated on off, Root gets on his knees and slog sweeps this one to deep mid-wicket. The ball bounces once and crosses the ropes. 50 up for England too.
On off, blocked.
Flatter and around off, Root shuffles and punches this one to deep covers for three this time.
On off, pushed to point for one.
FOUR! Sweep again, Four again. Full and tossed up on the middle pole, Root gets low again and sweeps this one to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On a good length and around off, Dan pushes this one to the cover region.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! LBW! That one was plumb and it is Ishant's 300th wicket in Test cricket. Only the third Indian pacer to achieve this feat as he joins Kapil Dev and Zaheer Khan in that list. He will be very happy with his milestone and he helps India get another wicket. Sharma bowls this one on a good length and just around off, comes into the right-hander slightly as he looks to flick this one. Lawrence misses and the ball hits him low on the pads. An appeal and the umpire does not take too long to raise his finger. Lawrence comes across and has a chat with Root and decides to review it. Ultra Edge shows a flatline and Ball Tracker is in...THREE REDS! Dan will have to walk back and England lose one review too. England lead by 299 runs.
On a good length and around off, Stokes defends this one out solidly.
Down the leg side this time, Stokes looks to flick this one but he misses it.
On a good length and outside off, bounces more than what Ben would have anticipated. But he leaves it be. A great over for Ishant. A wicket-maiden.

FOUR! Brilliantly played. Ashwin has his hands on his hips. How do you bowl to this man? Flighted and on off, Root reverse sweeps this one through backward point and there is no point chasing after this one. Will be a lost cause as it runs away to the ropes.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Short, around off, Root flicks it to deep square leg. Rotates the strike.
Flighted and on off, Stokes pushes this to the cover region.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Stokes gets off the mark now. Flatter and on the pads, flicked to square leg for a single. England lead by 305 runs now.
On the pads, Stokes turns it to the leg side and gets a single.
Good length ball around off, Root taps it behind point and rotates the strike.
Full on off and middle, Stokes defends it with a straight bat.

FOUR! Up and over! Full on middle and off, Stokes takes the aerial route and hits it over mid on for a boundary. It was a slower ball but it went like a tracer bullet once it connected with Stokes' willow.
Full around off, Stokes drives it straight to the man at short cover.

Good fielding but cannot stop the single. Full on middle, Stokes places it to the right of mid on. Rahane there covers a lot of ground and gets to the ball but cannot hold onto it. Allowing Stokes to take the run and keep the strike.

OUT! CAUGHT! The dangerous Ben Stokes is out of here and Ashwin gets his 3rd of the innings. England ahead in this game but India not giving up here. Flighted delivery outside off, Stokes looks to push it on the off side. The ball though drifts and turns just a fraction. A fraction is good enough to kiss the outside edge of the bat and go straight into the mitts of Rishabh Pant. England lose their 4th and they lead by 312!
Uppish but safe! Risky start from Pope. Floated on middle, Pope comes down the track and turns it to the leg side. Luckily for Ollie, it is wide of Gill at short leg.
Floated on middle and leg, Pope sweeps it to backward square leg.
Short on middle and leg, Pope keeps it out.
Flighted on middle, Pope comes down the track and turns it to the right of short mid-wicket. Kohli there dives and saves runs for his side.
Pope is off the mark! Flighted on middle and off, Pope sweeps it in front of square on the leg side and keeps the strike.
FOUR! Glorious! First boundary for Pope! Good length ball outside off, Pope leans forward and drives it on the up. He times it and places it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Now a brace! Fuller on middle, Pope flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Uppish but safe! Full on middle and leg, Pope flicks it away from the man at catching position on the on side. There is Pujara at deep mid-wicket. So just a single.
Full on middle and leg, Pope plays it to Rahane who is one of the three men at catching position on the on side.
Full on off, Pope pushes it to mid off.
Full on off and middle. This one shapes the other way around. Pope negotiates it well and keeps it out.

NOT OUT! Pope survives. The ball has come off his elbow and hence he reviewed it straightaway. Floated delivery pitching outside off and turning back in. Pope looks to play the reverse sweep but the ball hits him and lobs to short leg. Gill takes the catch and appeals. The umpire raises his finger. Pope reviews it and Ultra Edge finds nothing as the ball goes past the bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and that is missing the stumps.
Darted on middle, Pope keeps it out. Another No Ball from India. This has been a serious cause of concern for India in this game.

Aggression from Pope. He uses his feet and dances down the pitch. He does not time it well but hits it over the cow corner region. There is no one in the deep there. Washington Sundar runs in from deep mid-wicket and manages to pull it back before the ropes. Saves a run for his side.
Floated on middle, Root blocks it.
Tossed up on middle, Root reverse sweeps it behind point for one.

Pope now brings out the reverse sweep. Flighted on off and middle. Pope reverse sweeps it. Bumrah at backward point looks to stop it with his feet. Poor footballing skills from Bumrah sees the ball go behind and they get a couple.
In the air but safe! Pope overuses the reverse sweep. This is on middle, Pope gets a top edge and it lobs in the air. The ball though falls away from Ashwin.
NO BALL AND FOUR! Bumrah starts with a no ball and a boundary. Good length ball down the leg side, Root looks to flick but gloves it just wide of diving Pant and the ball races to the fence.
Length ball outside off, Root leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! India lose their second review. It looked to be going over the stumps to the naked eye and that is what has been shown on the Ball Tracker. Good length ball pitching outside off and coming back in. Root looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pad. There is a huge appeal but the umpire is not interested. Bumrah is certain he has his man. Kohli opts for the review. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge first shows no involvement of bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows the ball to be missing the leg pole. India lose their second review and Root survives.
Good length ball outside off. Root chops it to keeper on the bounce.
FOUR! Punched away! Shortish around off, Root punches it through backward point for a boundary. He has looked fabulous throughout this Test.
On off, Root keeps it out.
Good length ball pitching on off, Root looks to defend but misses.

Just short of Kohli this time. Flighted and around off, Pope looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the blade and goes towards Kohli at mid-wicket, who comes forward but is not able to grab this one.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Floated and on middle, Pope looks to defend this one but the ball takes the gloves and lobs towards the short leg fielder but it is short of him as well.
Outside off, Pope punches this one to point for a single.
On off, Root comes down the track and looks to push this one away but the ball takes the pads and rolls to the off side this time. They think about the single but decide not to, in the end.
Short and around off, Root dabs this one towards the third man region for a single.
Good length ball around off, Root taps it towards point for a single.
Low full toss on off and middle. Almost the yorker. Pope flicks it to short mid-wicket on a bounce.
Uppish but safe again! Full on middle and leg, Pope flicks it uppishly wide of Rohit Sharma who is at catching position on the leg side for one.
Full on middle and off, Root flicks it to square leg for a couple.

OUT! LBW! Bumrah gets his first of the innings and Root's innings comes to an end. Good length ball pitching around off. It reverses back in and stays low as well. Root looks to defend but the lack of bounce surprises him. The ball misses his bat and hits him plumb in front of the stumps. There is a mandatory appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Root knows he is a goner and does not waste the review. Half the side back in the hut for England. They lead by 342!

EDGED AND FOUR! Excellent ball but the rub of the green goes Buttler's way. Full around off and this one reverses away from Jos. He looks to defend off his front foot but the ball hits the inside edge of his bat and goes through the backward square leg region. Nadeem gives it a chase and dives but to no avail.
Tossed up on off and middle, Pope keeps it out.
Short on middle and off, Pope punches it through covers for a single.
Around leg, Buttler keeps it out.

NO BALL AND SIX! Excellent use of the feet from Buttler. He has hit it high and handsome over the ropes. Tossed up on middle and off, Buttler comes down the track and smokes it over the bowler's head for a biggie. Nadeem has overstepped again and Pant is telling him to watch out his front crease.
Flighted on off, Buttler keeps it out.
Tossed up around off, Buttler strokes it through point and gets a couple.
Flighted on the stumps, Buttler blocks it.
Fuller and on the off pole, Pope clips this one through mid-wicket for a single.

An appeal for LBW but it is turned down on this occasion. On a good length and on middle and leg, jags back in as well, Buttler looks for the clip away but misses and gets rapped on the pads. An enquiry but the umpire is unmoved. Was sliding down the leg side.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

Another full ball on off and middle, Jos whips this one to the left of short mid-wicket, where Rohit Sharma is stationed. He is not able to stop this one and Pujara mops up in the deep. A brace on this occasion.
Good length and outside off, Buttler shoulders arms this time around.
Another good length ball outside off, Buttler drives this one to the cover region this time.
Good length ball around off, Pope flat-bats it towards point for one.
Length ball outside off, Buttler plays it to point.
Length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler opens the gate and lets the ball carry to the keeper.
Full and coming in, Buttler defends it with a dead bat.
Length ball on off, Buttler defends it with a straight bat. TEA ON DAY 4!

FOUR! Good hands from Pope and he starts the final session of the Day with a bang. England showing what route they are looking to take. On a good length and outside off, Pope frees his arms and slams this one through the cover region and into the ropes.
On a good length and on off, Pope pushes this one to the cover region.
Short of a length and on middle, Pope clips this one to the mid-wicket fielder.
Another length ball around off, Pope taps this one to point. Looks for the single but does not go for it, in the end.
Ollie pushes this one to the cover region again, but for no runs this time.
Good length and around off, Ollie works this to covers again.
Short and on the pads, Buttler looks to pull but the ball takes the top edge and goes towards fine leg for a couple.
On middle, reverse swept to the backward point region for a couple again.
FOUR! That was not even a reverse sweep, it was a reverse cover drive. Flighted and on off, Pope reverses and slams this one through the cover region for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nadeem gets the wicket and it is his first one in this innings. Pope has played well in his small innings but he loses his wicket in trying to be aggressive. Flighted and on middle, Pope looks to reverse sweep this one again but the ball takes the top edge and lobs towards the cover region where Rohit Sharma takes a good catch. England lead by 371 runs.
Tossed up and around off, Bess comes down the track and lofts this one over Ashwin at mid on for a couple.
Flighted on leg, Bess clips this one to square leg for a single.
Good length ball in the channel of uncertainty. Bess looks to defend but misses.
Fuller on off and middle, Bess blocks it.
Low full toss on off, Bess defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and jagging back in from middle. Bess looks to defend but gets hit on the pad.
Angling in from good length area on middle. Bess turns it to square leg for a single.
Full on middle, Buttler blocks it.
On the pads, Bess pads it away!
Floated on the pads, Bess defends it.
Once again pitching outside leg. Bess pads it away.
Again on the pads, Bess is happy to pad it away.
Once again no shot offered to this one which is pitched outside leg.
Nadeem bowls another one outside leg. Bess pads it away.
Fuller on middle, Buttler pushes it to cover for one.
Full on middle, Bess defends it.
Good ball! Shortish ball outside off. Bess takes his eyes off the ball and ducks.
Full on middle, Bess keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Bess blocks it.
Just a single of the over. England are in no hurry at the moment. Full on off and middle, Bess defends it to mid on.
Down the leg side, Buttler paddles it but straight to short fine leg.
Another one down the leg side, Buttler paddles it to deep square leg for a single.
Down the leg side. Bess does not offer a shot and Pant too fails to hold onto the ball. It goes to the fence but won't cound as no shot was offered.
On the pads, Bess flicks it to the leg side and rotates.
Down the leg side, Buttler paddles it to the left of short fine leg.
Darted quicker on the leg side, Buttler looks to paddle sweep it the Tendulkar way but misses.

Fuller on middle and off. Bess looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge through gully. Washington Sundar in the deep runs to his left and manages to slide and pull it before the ropes. Saves a run for his side.
Full on off and middle, Buttler flicks it to square leg and gets a single to extend the lead to 382!
Good length ball outside off, Bess looks to defend but misses.
No urgency from either side here. Full on middle, Bess flicks it to deep square leg and rotates.
Good length ball on middle and off. Buttler defends it off the inner half of his bat.

Down the leg side, Buttler looks to flick but misses. England are in no rush here which is kind of a strange tactic. Probably looking to bat time as they feel they have enough runs on the board already.
Pitched outside leg, Bess looks to pad it away but the ball hits the forearm.
Around leg, Dom pads this one away.
Flighted on leg, worked to the fine leg region for a couple.
Down the leg side and Bess just leaves it alone.
On the leg pole, left alone by Dom again.
Flighted and on middle, kept out.
On a good length and on off, Jos pushes this one to covers for one.
Good length and on off, Dom pushes it back to the bowler.
On a good length and on middle, flicked to the leg side.
On a good length and on off, Bess flicks this one to the leg side.
On middle, pushed through mid on for a single.
On a good length and around off, Buttler pushes this one to the cover region.
Floated on off, Bess blocks this one.
On middle, pushed to the leg side.
On middle, flicked to the leg side again.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted on off, Bess sweeps this one to deep square leg for a single.
On middle, swept to the leg side again.
Flighted outside off, Bess lets it be.
Tossed up and on off, Dom keeps this one out.
Spun sharply there. Floated and outside off, spins away sharply as Bess looks to play at this one but misses.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On off, Bess keeps this one out.
NO BALL AND FOUR! Ashwin oversteps this time and Buttler also punishes him. Flatter around off, Jos goes on the back foot and punches this one to the cover region and into the ropes at the deep.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Flighted on middle, Buttler fends this one out.
Loopy and around the middle pole again, Buttler pushes this one to the mid on region.

An appeal for LBW but turned down by the umpire. Loopy and on middle, Jos gets on his knees and looks to sweep this one away to the leg side but he misses and gets rapped on the pads. An appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Kohli thinks about it and then opts against taking the review.

Another appeal but nothing doing from the umpire. Flighted and on off, Buttler looks to sweep again but misses and the ball takes the pads and goes to the off side. Ashwin appeals but to no avail. 5 runs off this over.
FOUR! The lead now moves to 397! Short and spinning away, Nadeem punches it through extra cover for a boundary.
Floated on off, Bess defends it to point.
FOUR! The lead moves past 400! Flighted outside off, Bess picks the length well and sweeps it over mid-wicket for a boundary.  The tourists now lead by 401!
Pitched outside leg, Bess looks to pad it away but the ball bounces a bit more and hits him on his arm.
Another one pitched outside leg, Bess pads it away.
Flatter on middle, Bess keeps it out.
Floated on leg, Buttler looks to defend but the ball lobs back to Ashwin off the pad.
On the pads, Buttler flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Short on off, Bess defends it on the leg side.
FOUR! Short, wide and punished! Bess looking really impressive with the bat. Short around off, Bess cuts through point for a boundary.
Floated outside off, Bess looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pad. Stifled appeal from the Indian players but nothing from the umpire.
On the stumps, Bess keeps it out.
Down the leg side. Buttler looks to paddle but it hits his glove, gets stuck on his pad and falls away from Pant.

OUT! STUMPED! Buttler departs and Nadeem gets his second of the game. Once again Nadeem bowls it outside leg, Buttler comes down the track and looks to hit it straight. He misses and Pant behind the stumps has an easy task. He makes no mistake.
This one keeps low. Floated outside off, the ball keeps low and Archer manages to push it to mid off.
This one turns viciously. Floated on the pads, Archer looks to flick but gets a leading edge. Luckily for Archer, it does not carry to the diving second slip fielder.
Floated on middle, Archer sweeps it to mid-wicket for a couple. Jofra will be glad ton get off the mark and not have a pair to his name.
Tossed up on off, Archer keeps it out.

OUT! The ball hit the pad first and once that was sure there was hardly anything that could have saved Bess. Bess' effort comes to an end. A good knock from the spinner. Shorter on off, Bess looks to defend but the bat gets stuck behind his pad. The ball hits his pad and a huge appeal follows. The umpire raises his finger. Bess takes the review. Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat involved. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shos all reds. 4-fer for Ashwin with that wicket.
Flighted on off, Leach keeps it out.
Tossed up off, Leach looks to defend but gets an outside edge. The ball though does not carry to the man at slip.
Flighted on off, JL defends it.
Floated on the stumps, Leach blocks it.
Tossed up on the stumps, Leach defends it.
Short and spinning away. Archer defends it to cover for a single.
Loopy ball on off and middle, Leach blocks it.
FOUR! In the air and in the gap! Flighted on middle and off, Leach comes down the track and hits it away from Ashwin at long on for a boundary.
Shorter on middle, Leach looks to defend but does so uppishly. Luckily for Leach it falls short of Rohit Sharma at short leg.
On the stumps, kept out.
FOUR! Edgy boundary but England will not mind it. Floated on off, Leach comes down the track and looks to hit it over but gets an outside edge which sees the ball go over the slip and to the fence.
Tossed up on middle, Archer keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Archer lofts it over cover for a single.
Flighted outside off, Leach swings but cannot connect.
On off, Leach keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Leach defends it.
On the stumps, JL blocks it.
Floated ball on off, Archer drives to mid off.
Flatter ball on the pads, Archer tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Floated ball on off, Leach defends it to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Flighted ball outside off, Leach pushes it to cover.
Shorter and on middle, Leach works it to the leg side.

OUT! TIMBER! Brilliantly bowled by Ashwin! He gets a 5-fer as well and it has been another good performance by them. Floated ball on off, Archer looks to flick it off the back foot but misses and the ball goes onto hit the timber.
Full ball on off, Anderson looks to play the reverse sweep but it goes to first slip.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! That's it! England's second innings is over! Terrific display from Ashwin! Loopy ball on middle, Anderson looks to flick but gets a leading edge which lobs back towards the bowler. Ashwin accepts it gleefully. ENGLAND BOWLED OUT FOR 178. INDIA NEED 420 RUNS TO WIN.
Anderson starts with a good length ball outside off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Full ball outside off, Sharma watches it carefully and then shoulders arms to it.
Another full ball outside off, Sharma has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma lets it go to the keeper.
Short ball around middle, Sharma looks to pull at first but then decides to let it go. Buttler hops and collects.
A maiden to start from Jofra Archer! Good length ball on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Leach starts with a flatter ball on off, Gill goes on his back foot and then defends it to point.
Floated ball outside off, Gill prods forward and then decides to leave it alone.
Slower through the air outside off, Gill shoulders arms to it.
Tossed up on middle, Shubman defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, Gill uses his feet and then looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Wonderful shot from Gill! Slightly short on middle, Gill goes on his back foot and then pulls it to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sharma hops and looks to defend but gets hit high on the bat.
On a length outside off, Sharma once again makes a leave.
PLAY AND A MISS! Not needed from Sharma! Good length ball outside off, Sharma looks to punch it off the back foot but misses as the ball keeps a little low.
Full ball on off, Sharma prods forward and then blocks it to the off side.
Full ball outside off, Sharma lets it go to Buttler.
Tossed up on off, Gill pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Superb timing from Gill! Flatter ball on middle and leg, Gill just times this through the mid-wicket region for a boundary. No chance for the fielder chasing after it.
FOUR! Flicked away nicely! Very full on the pads, Gill flicks it through the fine leg region for another boundary.
Floated ball outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
Full and on off, Gill pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on middle, Shubman defends it back to the bowler.
Full ball outside off, Sharma lets it through to the keeper.
Sharma is off the mark! Good length ball on off, Rohit taps it to point for a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Gill just plays it to the off side and takes a quick run.
FOUR! In the air but safe! Short ball on middle, Sharma looks to pull but it goes off the toe end of the bat towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
SIX! This time a lot more convincing! Short ball on middle, Sharma rocks back on the back foot and then pulls it over deep square leg for a maximum.
Short ball on the pads, Rohit pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Floated ball outside off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Sharma prods forward and then defends it to point.

OUT! TIMBER! What a ripper from Jack Leach! Just a ripper! That will get England going! Superb delivery and it sends Rohit Sharma back to the pavilion. Tossed up on middle, it spins away after pitching. Sharma prods forward to defend but misses and the ball goes onto hit the off stump. Wow, simply brilliant. Leach did not have a good time in the first innings but has started well in the second. India need 395 more.
Flatter ball on middle, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely timed and cut away! Short ball outside off, Pujara cuts it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Full on off, Pujara defends it out.
Good length and on middle, Gill flicks this one through mid-wicket for a single.
Full ball on the pads, Pujara flicks it to the deep mid-wicket region for a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Gill plays it back to the bowler.
Full ball on the pads, Gill pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, defended out.
On a length on off, Gill blocks it to cover.
Quicker on off, Pujara defends it to cover.
Tossed up on the pads, Pujara flicks it to backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara punches it to deep cover for a single.
Full ball on the pads, Gill nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on the pads, Gill is solid in defense.
Loopy ball outside off, left alone by Gill.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it out.
Back of a length ball around middle and leg, Pujara looks to tuck it on the leg side but hits his thigh pad and lobs to short leg.
On a length on middle, CP nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, defended out solidly.
Full ball on middle, Pujara drives it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on off, Pujara goes back in his crease and then blocks it to cover.
Full ball on middle, Gill pushes it to mid on.
Fuller on the pads, SG works it to mid-wicket.
Floated ball on off, punched back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on the pads, Shubman works it to square leg.
Tossed up on off, defended to silly point.
Flighted ball on the pads, Gill nudges it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Flatter ball on middle, Pujara plays it towards mid on for nothing.
Tossed up on middle, Pujara nudges it to backward square leg for a single.
Flighted ball on off, Gill uses his feet and then defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on middle, Gill works it to short mid-wicket.
Quicker on middle, tucked to short leg.
Flighted ball on middle, Pujara nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Pujara plays it to point.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
Tossed up outside off, CP prods forward and then lets it go to the keeper.
Flatter ball outside off, punched to cover.
Shorter and outside off, Pujara punches it though the extra cover region for a couple of runs.
Quicker on middle, Gill defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, Shubman goes on the back foot and then defends it out.
Flighted on middle, Gill works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on middle, Gill tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter and on middle, Pujara works it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter ball on off, Gill goes on his back foot and then defends it back to the bowler. STUMPS ON DAY 4.
Starts with a fuller length ball on the pads, Pujara nudges it behind square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Gill is away on Day 5 in style! A long hop around off, Shubman is on the back foot immediately as he pulls it delightfully to the deep mid-wicket fence. He won't let loose balls go unpunished.
Flatter and a touch shorter again, around off, Gill stays back and hits it in front of square leg for a couple. The siren goes off and it's a no ball.
Sliding down the leg side, this time Gill fails to work it off his pads.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball and defends it back.
Excellent leave. Full and flighted on off, turning away, Gill covers his stumps and allows it through.
Too full in length on off, Gill drives it firmly through the line but finds the cover fielder. Good first over for India, 8 runs off it!
Begins with a fuller length ball on off, slower in pace at 126 kph, Pujara is on the front foot in defense.
Lands it full and close to off again, Pujara plays it near to his body and pushes it with an angled bat to covers.
Good length ball angling in around off, Cheteshwar stays back and is solidly behind the line in defense.
Quietly played. Fullish and around off, Pujara eases it softly in the gap at covers for a quick run.
A bouncer first up to Gill. It's served around off and Shubman sits underneath it.

A wayward delivery. On a good length and wide outside off, further shaping away, Gill allows it through and Buttler has to dive to collect it in front of first slip. Troubled his keeper more than the batsman, Jofra!
Full and floated on off, Pujara advances down the track and drives it to the left of mid off for a run.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Loopy and full on middle, Gill draws forward and blocks it back safely.
A touch short and on off, Gill works it on the leg side but finds mid-wicket.
Ooops...this one keeps low after landing around off, Gill does well to go down low and keep it out to square leg for a run.
Flatter this time, around middle, defended back to the bowler. 50/1 are India.
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, shaping away slightly, with the shine, Gill offers no shot.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Gill stays on the back foot and gently plays it through cover-point. Straightaway calls two and gets them easily.
Angling in a full length ball on off, Gill brings down a straight bat and defends it back. The extra cover fielder moves to his right to make a diving stop.
Good length ball on middle, defended off the back foot to mid on.
Pitches it up and in the line of the stumps, Gill uses his wrists and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a run. No issues whatsoever so far for India.
On a good length close to off, Pujara sticks back and defends it close to his body. It rolls to covers and a loud shout of no follows.
Extra flight, it drops full around leg, Gill pushes it down to mid on.
Floated and full around off, Gill gets on the front foot and defends it watchfully.
Leach pushes it quicker through the air, flat and on middle, Gill turns it off his pads to the leg side, finds mid-wicket.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

PITCH MISBEHAVES! Excellent delivery. This one lands full and around off, Gill is forward in defense but the ball shoots up and spins past the outside edge. Beats the keeper and slip for FOUR BYES! That will sow a seed of doubt in the batsmen's minds.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball around off and defends it safely.
Good length ball on off, Pujara stays back and defends it down on the off side.
Full this time, around off, Pujara pushes it off his front foot to short extra cover.
Archer delivers a knuckle delivery, slower in pace and very full on middle, Pujara does well to defend it back.
Bangs in a bouncer around middle and leg, Pujara lets it be with ease. Archer is trying to mix up his length and pace.
Fuller length delivery, close to off, Pujara defends it near his front pad and pushes it to covers.
Back of a length delivery outside off, coming slowly off the surface, Pujara hangs on the back foot and taps it down towards point.
A tossed up delivery but too full in length on middle, Gill jams it down to mid on.
Flatter and a touch shorter on off, Shubman goes back and punches it through covers for a run.

OUT! First wicket falls on Day 5 for India. Beauty of a delivery. Leach lands it full and on middle, gives it a good toss, Pujara gets forward and tries to work it on the leg side at the last moment. But it jumps, takes the shoulder of his bat and Stokes takes a superb catch stretching to his left at first slip. Pujara will be a little disappointed with himself, had he played it out with a straight bat, then he could have defended it down despite the extra bounce.
Flighted and full outside off, Virat is on the front foot in defense.
Flatter and shorter on off, Kohli goes on the back foot this time and defends it to the off side.
Very full and close to off, Virat defends it to covers to end the over, a successful one for England.
FOUR! Lovely footwork! Gill dances down the track to a full ball outside off and drills his drive down the ground to long off for a boundary.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

FOUR! Gill is on the attack, he doesn't want Bess to adjust. Shubman is down the track in a flash, takes it on the full and swings it over mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep attempts for a catch but it goes wide of his outstretched left hand and finds the fence.
Works it on the leg side, finds the gap at mid-wicket and crosses.
Strides forward to a full ball and helps it towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller and outside off, Kohli leans forward and plays it with soft hands to covers for one. 10 from Bess' first this morning!
Too full in length on off, Kohli drives but finds the cover fielder.
Shortish and outside off, VK gets back and plays it late, finds backward point.
Slower through the air, good flight, it lands full around leg, Kohli defends it to mid-wicket.
Good running between the wickets! Kohli gets on the back foot and taps a short delivery to the right of point for a brisk run.
Loopy and very full on middle, Gill defends it back off his front foot.
Slightly short and around off, turning away, Gill covers his stumps and allows it through.
Flighted ball landing full on off, Kohli leans forward and wrists it past short mid-wicket for a single.

SIX! This one is dispatched! Positivity is in his DNA. Fuller in length and outside off, Gill wears his skates again and dismisses it over long on. 'Shot boy', says Kohli from the other end. Impressive!
Ouch, that would have hurt! Short delivery on middle, Gill pulls it across the line and it hits the short leg fielder on the right leg.
Walks down the track to take it on the full and eases it to long on for a run.
Allows the ball to turn back in and then deflects it down to fine leg for one.
Quicker and flatter on off, defended off the back foot by Gill. 9 from this over, 19 from Bess so far on Day 5.
Strides forward and drives a full ball to covers. The fielder there dives and makes a partial stop. Two taken.
Fuller and on off, Kohli gets forward and pushes it with an angled bat to covers for one.
Flatter and shorter on off, turning away, Gill is on the back foot as he defends.
Short again, outside off, Gill cuts it to point where the fielder makes a tumbling stop. They cross for a run.
Quick run again! Fullish and on off, Kohli plays a punchy off drive and rushes to the other end as the mid off fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end.
Flighted and full on middle, Gill flicks it behind square leg but finds the fielder. India continue to score freely, 5 from this over. Good positive cricket!
Loopy ball on off, Kohli walks down the track and flicks, finds short mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball outside off, Kohli whips it across the line but again finds short mid-wicket.
Loopy and outside off, on the shorter side and spinning in, Kohli gets back and works it towards square leg for a run.
Advances down the track to make it into a half-volley and knocks it down to long on for a run.
Fuller and on off, Kohli forces it down to deepish mid on for a single.
Once again Gill uses his feet and pushes a full ball to the right of mid on for one.
Flighted and full on middle, Gill defends it to mid on.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Slower through the air, nicely flighted and full around leg, Gill picks it off his pads and whips it to the deep mid-wicket fence. Moves to 49!
Fuller and on off, Gill drives it down to mid on.
Loopy and full around leg, Shubman flicks it across the line but finds short mid-wicket.
Sliced away! Loopy again, full and spinning away, Gill is a bit upright as he tries to drive and it takes the outer half before rolling to backward point.

FIFTY FOR GILL! Yet another outstanding knock by the young man and he continues to impress one and all. He reaches there by playing it out to the left of backward point for a single. India would want him to carry on!
Fuller in length and on off, Gill plays near his front pad and works it to short mid-wicket.

OUT! STUMPS SHATTERED! Anderson has done it! Experience trumps inexperience! Jimmy hurls in a full length ball close to off and gets it to reverse back into the batsman. Gill is forward to defend but leaves a big gap between his bat and pad. The ball sneaks through and destroys the stumps behind. Anderson roars in delight, England get a big wicket and are 7 away from taking the lead in the series.
Fuller and wide outside off, swinging again, Rahane makes a leave.

NOT OUT! Lovely delivery by Anderson again! He makes the ball do all the talking and this one stays low as well. A full ball on off, nipping in, Rahane tries to defend but it beats the toe end of his bat and pings him on the front pad. They appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Root has a word with his bowler and then opts for the DRS. Flat line on the Ultra Edge, the impact is with the umpire's call and it's hitting the stumps. Rahane survives.

OUT! Off stump goes for a walk! Anderson is on fire! Rahane bags a duck and England are on top! Jimmy is putting in a masterclass of reverse swing bowling. Wow! This one is identical to the delivery which got Gill. On and around off, a fuller length ball which nips back in sharply. Rahane is forward in defense but he also has a big gap between his bat and pad. The ball finds its way through and uproots the off stump. Five balls, two wickets and Anderson is doing it for England, yet again.
Anderson switches to 'round the wicket and angles in a full ball on off, Pant has his bat down in time in defense.
Fuller and around leg, Kohli drives it down to mid off.
Loopy and full around off, Virat presses forward in defence.
Too full and on middle, Kohli drives but finds silly point.
Sharp spin as it lands around off. Kohli takes a big stride forward and makes a leave.
Strides forward again and pushes it towards point.
Short and outside off, cut to point where the fielder misfields and the batsmen cross. Anderson vs Kohli coming up!
Movement in the air, full and around off, Kohli defends it to the off side from the toe end of his bat.
Plays it nice and late. Full and around off, shaping in, Kohli takes his front leg forward and works it wide of mid on for a run.
Fuller and on off, Pant gets forward and defends it watchfully.
FOUR! Off the mark with a boundary. Full and outside off, Pant drives it firmly and finds the gap at covers. Not much footwork but good hand-eye coordination!
On a length and outside off, Pant taps it down to the right of the cover fielder.
Anderson keeps it full and around off, Pant has his bat down as he pushes it defensively to mid on.
Flighted and full on middle, Kohli defends it by getting forward.
Flatter and fuller on leg, Kohli flicks it in front of square leg and gets three runs.
Floated and full outside off, Pant gets forward and drives it through covers for a run. Wants the second run as well but Kohli sends him back.
Short and wide outside off, Kohli cuts it towards cover-point and the point fielder runs across to make a partial diving stop. The batsmen take a run.

Play and a miss! Full and flighted outside off, Pant tries to play the reverse sweep but misses and it goes off his arms to the off side. Needs to be careful while playing that shot from the rough outside off.
Too full in length and on off, Pant pushes it in the gap at covers for a run.
Good length ball angling into the batsman, around off, Pant defends it back.
Fuller length ball shaping back into the batsman, Pant drives it confidently to mid off. Is Jimmy setting up Pant for an outswinger?
Around off on a length, straightening a bit, Pant defends it from the crease.
Anderson bowls it from wide of the crease and angles in a full ball on middle, Pant flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
Here comes the outswinger!!! Anderson hurls it in the channel outside off, Pant ends up pushing and missing inside the line.
Fuller and on off, Pant defends it towards cover-point. A maiden by Anderson.
Fuller and outside off, driven back to the bowler.
Shortish and on off, turning away, Kohli gets back, opens the face and guides it to backward point for a run.
FOUR! Fine shot! Leach flights it outside off, Pant shimmies down the track and eases his drive through cover-point.
Loopy and full outside off, it's a mere push at extra cover and Pant collects a single.
Flighted and full on off, drifting in, Kohli is forward as he defends it near his front pad.
Flighted again, full and on off, Kohli stretches forward and defends it under his watchful eyes.
Good length delivery outside off, shaping away, Pant reads it well and allows it through.
Beaten! A length ball close to off, Pant tries to defend but it holds its line and beats the outside edge.

OUT! Soft dismissal! Anderson bags his third wicket and Pant is gone! This Test match is now completely in favour of England. Jimmy steams in from 'round the wicket and hurls in a length ball around off. It lands and probably shapes away a bit, Pant presses forward and pushes it uppishly off the outer edge to the right of Root at short cover. A simple catch for the English skipper and India now have lost half their side.
Greets the new batsman with an outswinger outside off, Sundar allows it through to the keeper.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Pitches it up and around off, Sundar defends it compactly to the off side. A wicket maiden, what a spell from Anderson!
FOUR! A gentle loosener, a juicy full toss around off, Kohli drives it through covers for a boundary. Anderson is bowling so well from one end and this is the last thing you want from the other end.
Floated full ball on off, Kohli defends it with the spin to the leg side.
Short and on middle, Kohli pulls it through backward square leg. Archer chases and pulls it back near the fence. Three taken. Poor bowling by Bess.
Floated and full on off, Sundar is on the front foot in defense.

OUT! Bess strikes. He finally gets his line and length right and the rest of the work is done by the pitch. It's around off, turning and bouncing away from the batsman, Sundar tries to defend but fails to do so. It goes past the outside edge, Buttler collects and appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Root takes the DRS and the Ultra Edge finds a spike. Wicket number 6 goes down for India.
Tossed up ball on middle, Ashwin defends it to end the over.
Lands it on a length and around off, Kohli plays it late and pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Identical to the last delivery, once again Kohli plays it with gentle hands and keeps it out to backward point.
Good length ball close to off, Kohli is on the back foot as he defends it back towards the bowler.
Pitches it up and outside off, Kohli takes his front leg forward to cover the line and movement before making a leave.
Fuller and on middle, Kohli flicks it behind square leg and takes a single.
Good length ball and close to off, Ashwin sticks back and defends it to the off side.
Flighted and down the leg side, Kohli turns it behind square leg for a single.
Uses his feet and drives it wide of mid off for a single.
Floated and full on middle, Kohli dances down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Flatter and a bit shorter on off, Ashwin goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Floated and around off, Ashwin walks forward and then makes a late adjustment to play it out safely to the off side.
Tossed up ball landing full on middle, Ashwin drives it down to mid on.
Full on middle, Kohli flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Good shot! Full again on middle, Kohli lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Kohli flicks it through square leg for a single.
OUCH! Bouncer on off, Ashwin tries to sway away from it but gets it off the gloves. It doesn't carry to the keeper. A good effort delivery by Archer.
Bouncer outside off, Ashwin sways away from it.
Back of a length on off, Ashwin blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Full toss on middle, Kohli makes full use of it and heaves it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Another full toss, this time around off, Kohli forces it down the ground and bags consecutive boundaries.
FOUR! Make it a hat-trick of boundaries! Bess is struggling big time to land his deliveries. Kohli fetches it on the full from around off and uses his lovely wrists to whip it through wide mid on.
Flighted and full on middle, Virat gets forward and flicks it to short leg.
Too full in length around leg, Kohli knocks it down to long on for a run.
A long hop on the leg stump line, Ashwin gets back and pulls it through backward square leg for a single. A very poor over by Bess comes to an end, 14 runs from it!
Archer digs in another bouncer to Ashwin who does well to evade it. The English speed merchant is trying to push Ashwin deep inside the crease and probably set him up for a yorker.
A length ball outside off, Ashwin stays on the back foot and plays it down to point.

Yet another blow on the right hand! Archer is making Ashwin's life difficult. He bangs in a shortish ball on middle and it bounces extra as it approaches the batsman, Ashwin tries to defend but it hits him on the right forehand.
FOUR BYES! Archer is bowling relentlessly at Ashwin. Digs in a terrific bouncer, well-directed, Ashwin tries to duck but it takes his helmet and balloons behind the keeper for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on middle, Ashwin stands tall inside the crease and defends it down in front of short leg.
A touch short and on off, Ashwin defends it from the back foot to short extra cover. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 5!
Starts with a very full ball on middle, it's served from wide of the crease, Kohli defends it from the front foot.
Leans forward to a full ball and pushes it to covers.
Too full and on off, Kohli plays a wristy drive but finds the cover fielder.
Loopy and full on middle, Virat lunges and blocks it down safely.
Full and around off, spinning away, Kohli gets forward with an angled bat and pushes it to the right of gully.
Flatter this time, a touch short and on off, Kohli goes back and punches it to the left of the cover fielder.
Some movement for the bowler but the line is around leg and it goes further down, Ashwin tries to flick but misses.
Right on the mark this time. Full and close to off, shaping back in, Ashwin plays it near his body and defends it back.
Once again Jimmy probes with a delivery around off, getting it to reverse back into the batsman, Ashwin shows good technique as he blocks it to the off side.
Seeing Ashwin getting too comfortable on the front foot, Anderson digs in a short ball around off. Ash does well to drop his wrists and it goes off his right shoulder to slip.
Play and a miss! Good length delivery outside off, going straight on, Ashwin pushes inside the line and misses.
EDGY FOUR! Anderson hurls across a length delivery outside off, getting it to shape away, Ashwin flirts inside the line again and edges it wide of slip for a boundary.
Stretches forward to a full ball and defends it to covers.

FOUR! A fine shot by Kohli and he moves to 49! Full and flighted on middle, Virat walks forward and brings his bottom hand into play. Superbly executed on drive and it runs away to the long on boundary.
Leach goes flatter and shorter on off, Virat defends it off his back foot.
Full and floated on off, turning away, Kohli is forward and defends it with the spin to the off side.
Full and wide outside off, an easy leave from Virat.
Quicker and fuller on leg, Kohli helps it off his pads to backward square leg. Looks for a run but is sent back.
Angles in a length ball on off, Ashwin defends it with a straight bat. The pitch map suggests that England have bowled 38 percent deliveries short to Ashwin. Definitely some plan against him.
Slightly up and around off, Ashwin pushes it off his front foot to covers.
Good length ball outside off, Ashwin takes a little stride forward and works it wide of short mid-wicket for a single.
In the channel outside off, Kohli has nothing to do with it.
On a good length and outside off, a hint of away shape there, Kohli covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Good length delivery again, outside off, Kohli plays it with an angled bat to backward point.
Fuller and on middle, Ashwin walks forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. Wants the second run but Virat is not interested.
Floated and full around off, Kohli strides forward and defends it to the off side.
Fullish and close to off, VK takes a big stride forward and defends.
Spinning away after landing on off, Kohli allows it through to the keeper.
A touch short and on off, Virat goes on the back foot and taps it down to point.
A nicely tossed up ball, landing full and around off, Kohli presses forward and defends it safely.
Anderson starts this over with a short ball on off, Ashwin pulls it well in front of square leg and takes a single.
Full and on off, angling in, Kohli defends it back to the bowler.
Keeps it full again, around off, Kohli is solidly behind the line as he defends it to covers.

FIFTY FOR KOHLI! Fuller length ball on off, Kohli uses his wrists and turns it through square leg for a single. Fine knock by the Indian skipper, his 24th in Tests and 7th while batting in the fourth innings! He would be aiming to build a strong partnership with Ashwin and help India salvage a draw.
Good length ball outside off, Ashwin pushes inside the line and misses.
Fuller and on off, defended to the off side to end the over.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, defended off the front foot.
Flighted and full around off, Kohli drives but fails to beat the diving attempt of the cover fielder.
Fuller in length and outside off, driven off the outer half towards point.
Pushes a full ball in the gap at covers for a single.
Shortish and close to off, Ashwin cuts it to backward point.
Angling into the batsman from around off, Kohli defends it.
Oohhh... a cross-seam delivery, landing on a length around middle, Kohli tries to defend and it takes the top half of his bat.
Uses the angle of the bowler and defends a full ball to short mid-wicket.
In the zone outside off, on a good length, Kohli offers no shot.
Back of a length ball on off, Kohli stands tall and steers it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Plays it nice and late. It's on a length and close to off, Virat drops it down with an angled bat to backward point.
Flighted and full, too wide outside off, an easy leave for Ashwin.
Full and around off, drifting in, Ashwin defends it to the off side.

NOT OUT! A tossed up ball landing around leg and straightening from there, Ashwin walks forward and tries to flick but misses. It goes off the pads to the on side and they cross. Root has a word with his bowler and the keeper before taking the referral. The Ball Tracker shows that the impact is with the umpire's call and it's going over the stumps.
Loopy and full around off, Kohli tries to defend but gets a soft outside edge. It sneaks past Stokes at first slip and they take a couple.
Loopy and full on middle, VK defends it by getting on the front foot.
Leach is on the shorter side this time, it's outside off and Kohli plays it towards backward point.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Ashwin stays back and plays it down to covers.
Once again Ashwin stays back to a shortish ball and pushes it to covers.
A good length delivery this time, close to off, Ashwin is forward as he plays it to the off side.
On a driving length outside off, some away movement after landing, Ashwin covers his stumps and allows it through.
Fuller and on off, getting closer to the stumps, Ashwin is right behind the line as he defends it to covers.
Good length ball on off, angling in, Ashwin works it around off his pads to mid-wicket. A maiden.
Full and flighted around leg, Kohli flicks it wristily through mid-wicket for three runs.
Shortish and on off, Ashwin hangs on the back foot and punches it to covers.
Leans forward to a full ball and pushes it towards wide second slip.
Flighted and full on off, Ashwin is nicely forward in defense.
Fullish and on off, Ashwin pushes it through the line, finds covers.
Tosses it up and lands full on off, spinning away, Ashwin defends it off his front foot to covers.
FOUR! Sweet timing and crisp placement! Back of a length delivery outside off, Kohli stands tall inside the crease and punches it through the gap at covers.
Sliding down the leg side, Kohli tries to flick but misses.
Edgy! Too full in length and on off, Kohli tries to flick but it takes a slight leading edge and rolls to mid off.
Fuller in length and outside off, Kohli strides forward and defends it to covers.
Fuller length ball on middle, Virat flicks it through square leg for a single.
This one stays low! Full and on off, Ashwin does well to bring his bat down as he defends it off the inner half to short mid-wicket.
Flighted and full around off, Kohli gets forward, opens the face of the bat and guides it past second slip for a run.

OUT! England have the breakthrough! Leach drags his length short and serves it close to off, Ashwin is tempted to play the square cut but it's too close to his body. There is some extra bounce as well and the outside edge is induced. Excellent reflex catch by Buttler and Leach gets his third wicket. The 105-ball stand is broken and Kohli now will have to rely on the tail for support.
Fullish and on off, Nadeem defends it from the outer half to the off side.
Tossed up ball landing full on middle, Nadeem defends it to the leg side.
Fuller and on off, defended with soft hands to the off side.
Skidding off the surface outside off, Nadeem picks it and makes a leave.
Good length ball close to off, Kohli pushes it with an angled bat in the gap at point. Not taking the run.
FOUR! Thumped! Short in length and on middle and off, Kohli swivels on the back foot and pulls it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Good length delivery outside off, Kohli defends it by taking the bottom hand off the handle.
Fullish and outside off, Kohli pushes it gently to covers.
A bouncer around off, Kohli offers no shot and lets it be. England would look for another dot to have Nadeem on strike for the next over.
DOT! A length ball outside off, Kohli walks across the stumps but pushes it straight to backward point.
Beaten! Full and flighted on off, Nadeem tries to defend but it spins past his blade.
Identical to the last delivery, some extra bounce, this time Nadeem offers no shot.
Loopy and full on off, Shahbaz defends it close to his front pad.
Fuller and on middle, it's defended uppishly past silly point.
Again uppish but safe! Floated and full on off, Nadeem advances down the track and looks to defend. Does so uppishly and it goes quickly past silly point again.
Quicker and flatter outside off, Nadeem allows it through to the keeper.
FOUR! A length delivery outside off, Kohli gets on the front foot and slightly opens the face of his bat to guide it towards third man for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, pushed in the gap at covers. No run taken.

OUT! Sound of timber and heartbreak for India! Kohli is cleaned up! Stokes hunts down the big fish. He delivers it on a length around off and it stays low after pitching. Kohli tries to defend but it goes under his bat and obliterates the off pole. Virat shakes his head as he returns. Stokes is all smiles. England are two wickets away from going 1-0 up in the series!
Full in length and outside off, left alone by Sharma.
Good length ball on middle and off, Ishant is squared up as he defends it down.
Fuller and on off, Ishant does well this time to push it safely towards cover-point. End of a successful over for Ben!
Loopy and full on off, Nadeem defends it off his front foot to the off side.
Quicker and flatter on middle, Nadeem goes on the back foot and defends it off the outer half towards silly point.

OUT! A relay catch and Leach gets his fourth wicket! Full and flighted ball on off, Nadeem gets forward to defend but it spins away slightly to take an outside edge. It goes behind and clips the pads of Buttler. Burns at second slip sticks his left hand out and then catches it in the second attempt. End is nigh for India!
FOUR! Walks down the track to a full ball and swings it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR BYES! Spin and bounce from outside off, Bumrah tries to slog sweep but misses. It beats the keeper as well and goes to the fence behind.
Lunges forward and jams down a fuller length ball around off.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends it from the back foot.
Archer digs in a short ball on middle, Ishant jumps and fends it off. It goes aerial but doesn't carry to short mid-wicket.
A well-directed bouncer and Ishant is in all sorts of trouble. Somehow he fends it off uppishly and this time it falls safely to the right of short leg.
A corker of a yorker on middle, Ishant does well to have his bat down in time. Digs it out and saves his toes.

NOT OUT! Archer digs in a short ball on middle, Ishant is on his toes as he tries to defend. Suddenly some sound of bails falling comes. Everyone thought that Ishant has stepped on the stumps but no one is sure. The onfield umpires take it upstairs and the replays show that the bails came off without any touch from the batsman. Bizarre!
Shortish and on off, Ishant jumps and turns it behind square leg for a run.
Looks to defend off the front foot but it takes the inside edge and strikes him on the pads.
FOUR! Fetches a full ball from outside off and sweeps it behind square leg for a boundary.
Too full in length and outside off, left alone.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Loopy and full around off, Ishant draws forward and defends it down safely.
Flatter and fuller on middle, defended back Ishant.

OUT! Edged and taken! ENGLAND WIN BY 227 RUNS! Brilliant delivery by Archer. He hurls across a good length ball around off and gets it to shape away. Bumrah is squared up in defense and edges it behind to the keeper. Buttler makes no mistake and the English camp is celebrating.
